title: juicy supper meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower lettuce salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a salad bowl in the order listed. Cover and chill for several hours.
Toss before serving.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: granola
directions: Mix thoroughly and put onto cookie sheet and in 300° oven. Turn every 10 minutes for 1 hour.
Store in Tupperware.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Crush potato chips on bottom of pan.
Spread.
Cut up chicken on top of chips.
Mix chicken soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise, chopped eggs, onion, pimento and celery.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: prairie fruitcake
directions: Cream together the first four ingredients. Mix in the applesauce. Add the baking soda, salt and spices. Blend in the flour and the water. Stir in remaining ingredients, except extra brown sugar. Grease and flour a 9 x 13 inch pan. Pour batter into pan and top with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Generously butter an 8-inch pie pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy. Beat in sugar, 1 teaspoon at a time, and continue beating until stiff and glossy, about 10 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Pile into a pie pan, pressing meringue up against the side.
Bake 1 hour. Turn off the oven; leave meringue in oven with door closed 1 hour. Remove from oven and cool.
Melt chocolate in hot water over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in vanilla.
In a chilled bowl, beat whipping cream until stiff, then fold in the chocolate mixture.
Pile into the meringue shell and chill at least 12 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream, chopped nuts or chocolate curls.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix the yogurt and Cool Whip in mixing bowl.
Pour the contents into the pie crust.
Shape and then top with fresh fruit. Freeze until ready to eat.
Remove pie from freezer approximately 1 hour prior to serving.
Um um good!

title: chicken imperial
directions: Blend crumbs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Combine garlic and butter.
Dip chicken in butter mixture; then roll into crumbs, coating thoroughly.
Roll each piece into firm roll; skewer with a toothpick.
Arrange in a baking pan.
Squeeze lemon juice over chicken; drizzle remaining butter over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party pork chops
directions: Place pork in a single layer in baking pan.
Place 1 onion slice topped with one lemon slice on center of each chop.
Blend remaining ingredients; spoon over each chop.
Cover pan tightly. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until pork is tender. Yield:
8 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake an unfilled pie crust at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain tomatoes on paper towels, then add to pie crust. Add chopped onions and toss. Mix cheese and mayonnaise. Cover tomato mixture. Top with Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add meat.
Let set. Heat oil in large frying pan and brown meat.
If not tender, cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes at low heat. Turn heat up and add veggies. Cook about 10 minutes.

title: onion dill bread
directions: Mix together yeast, flour, baking soda, salt and egg.
In separate pan, mix together warm water, cottage cheese, sour cream, sugar, onion, dill and butter.
Mix together dry and wet mixtures. Knead dough on floured surface until elastic (10 to 15 minutes). Put dough into lightly greased bowl and grease top lightly.
Cover bowl with clean cloth.
Let rise until doubled (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: fresh apple cake i
directions: Beat sugar and eggs; add oil and mix well.
Add sifted flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add vanilla, nuts, coconut and apples. This will be thick; so stir by hand at this point.
Pour into a greased and floured bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool cake for 20 minutes and turn out.
Pour Brown Sugar Icing over cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine rice, seasoning packet from rice mix and hot water. Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper and place over rice mixture.

title: kix or cheerios toffee
directions: In a large skillet, heat the sugar and butter to a boil.

Boil over medium heat for about 10 minutes or until mixture caramelizes (becomes light brown and thickened). Remove from heat. Stir in cereal until well coated. Turn into ungreased baking sheet and spread mixture evenly.
Cool and refrigerate. Break into pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine in saucepan the first 5 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts. Cook, stirring frequently, to hard crack or until small amounts separate into hard brittle threads when tested in very cold water. Add vanilla; pour into buttered sheet pan.
Cool, remove and break up.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in water.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and cloves.
Stir into egg mixture.
Mix in pumpkin and pecans.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans (9 x 5-inch).
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
No frosting is needed. Cake will be moist in center similar to brownies.

title: chicken curry
directions: In large skillet brown mushrooms and onion in butter, remove and set aside. In same skillet brown chicken in oil, add broth. Cover and cook 45 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken from skillet, combine flour and curry powder with liquid remaining in pan. Cook until just thickened, then add mushroom mixture, apple, half and half and chicken. Heat through. Serve with rice and desired accompaniments: chutney, coconut, chopped peanuts, raisins or crisp bacon bits. Yield: 5 or 6 servings.

title: cucumber dip or filling
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Chill.

title: wedged potatoes
directions: Wedge unpeeled potatoes; lay potatoes in baking pan, unpeeled skins down.
Brush with oil mixture several times.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until crispy.

title: fat free veggie pizza bites
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Unroll pizza crust and press into bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 8 to 11 minutes.
Let cool.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, dressing and Parmesan cheese. Mix well.
Spread over cooked crust.
Sprinkle broccoli florets, squash, red bell pepper, carrot and green onions over cheese mixture.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until cold.
Just before serving, cut into squares.
Makes 48 squares.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute chicken livers and sausage until browned.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion, celery, green onion, parsley, garlic and bell pepper.
Saute until tender.
Add thyme, basil, chicken livers and sausage.
Mix well. Stir in salt, pepper and chicken broth.
Cook rice according to package directions and add to sausage mixture.
Heat on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Serves 8.

title: country rabbit
directions: Coat rabbit pieces with seasoned flour.
Brown well in hot oil in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add small amount of hot water. Arrange bacon slices over rabbit.
Cover skillet; cook over low heat until rabbit is tender, adding water, if necessary.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (do not salt). Pick meat off bone and set aside. Save broth. Melt margarine and stir into cornbread stuffing. In a separate bowl, mix mushroom soup, chicken soup and a can of saved broth. In a greased 9 x 13-inch dish, put a layer of stuffing crumbs, then a layer of chicken and then a layer of the soup mixture. Repeat layers. Top with crumbs and bake at 350° until brown (45 minutes to 1 hour). Do not salt.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute eggplant, onion and zucchini in oil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cover, reduce heat to low and cook for 20 minutes until soft.
Transfer to a mixing bowl to cool.

title: microwave bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large glass bowl.
Heat in microwave for about 20 minutes at High.
Stir after 10 minutes.
If cheese is not fully melted after 20 minutes, heat for an additional 5 minutes.
Makes 30 servings.

title: mexican fiesta salad
directions: Make tossed salad as usual. Just before serving, add Fritos and toss with dressing.

title: lo-cal banana milkshake
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Add 2 to 3 ice cubes and whirl. Serve and enjoy.
Yields 1 serving (1 1/2 cups); 120 calories per serving.
Exchanges: 1 skim milk and 1 fruit.

title: maple coconut bars
directions: In a bowl, beat butter at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until combined.
Add egg and maple flavoring.
Beat at low speed just until combined.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture; mix until blended. Stir in 1 cup finely chopped coconut and chopped nuts.
In another pan, combine melted butter and remaining 1/2 cup coconut.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine eggs, soup, cheese, onion and mayonnaise.
Pour over green beans. Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over dish.
Pour melted butter over casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or bubbly. Serves 8.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Drain broccoli after it has been cooked.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Combine cheeses, broccoli and margarine, then add stuffing, eggs, salt and pepper.
Roll in balls and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen strawberry squares
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, nuts and butter.
Spread evenly in pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and crumble up.

title: risotto
directions: In frypan, brown meat and drain.
Add tomato paste, sugar, salt, pepper; mix.
In separate pan melt margarine, add rice and onion.
Coat thoroughly stirring with wooden spoon until yellow and add wine or 1/4 cup broth until absorbed.
Lower heat and stir in all remaining ingredients.
Place in Pam sprayed casserole and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
This is a popular church supper dish. Also excellent stuffing for peppers.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix all ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Cut into pieces.

title: no-bake chocolate bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over simmering water. Off heat, stir in remaining ingredients, except dredging sugar, in order listed.
As mixture stiffens, use hands to blend well. Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in confectioners sugar.
Let ripen 1 to 2 days before serving.
Makes 2 dozen.
Each bonbon contains about 95 calories.

title: turkey-rice salad
directions: In 1-quart bowl combine turkey, rice, celery, onions and red pepper.
In a small bowl thoroughly combine mayonnaise, sour cream, parsley, lemon juice, mustard and seasoning.
Pour dressing over salad and toss well to coat.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Toss again just before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 2 servings.

title: company blueberry pancake for two
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Blend together flour, milk, salt and eggs.
Fold in blueberries.
Melt butter in a heavy square casserole or black iron skillet.
Pour batter into sizzling butter.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and squeeze lemon juice over the pancake.
Sprinkle liberally with powdered sugar. Serve right from the casserole.
Recipe doubles nicely.
Is very good served with vanilla ice cream.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbs, 3 Tbsp. sugar and butter.
Press firmly onto bottom of 9 inch spring form pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into hot greased pan. Bake at 425° until top is browned.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook sausage, then add to rest of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or in crock-pot for a longer time.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in large bowl with wooden spoon.
Mix in remaining ingredients and bake in greased loaf pan for 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Take out of pan. Can also add 1 cup raisins if you like.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Dump all together and stir well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Cut grapes in half.
Peel and slice kiwis.
Cut oranges into small pieces.
Place fruit into large glass bowl in following order:
grapes, sliced bananas, drained peaches, raspberries, oranges and kiwi.
Pour orange juice over fruit.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: carameled lima beans
directions: Cover lima beans with water; cook until done.
Season with salt.
Brown 1 1/2 cups sugar in heavy skillet.
Very slowly, stirring with wooden spoon continuously, add butter.
Blend in flour; add bean juice.
If not enough, add water.
Mix in 3 tablespoons vinegar.
Add beans, a little at a time.

title: apple griddlecakes
directions: Sift into mixing bowl the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Place milk, egg, soft fat, apples and sugar in blender. Cover container of blender and turn on.
Run until apples are finely chopped, about 5 seconds.
Pour blended mixture over sifted flour mixture.
Stir until barely mixed.
Bake on hot greased, griddle, using about 2 tablespoons batter per cake.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake(or earthquake cake)
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake following box directions and pour on top of nuts and coconut.
Mix confectioners sugar and cream cheese together.
Add vanilla flavoring and melted oleo. Pour on top of cake.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini cake(best ever)
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt, mixing well.
Set aside.
Beat together salad oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and sherry.
Add flour mixture little by little.
Add zucchini and lemon peel.
Stir to blend.
Fold in nuts and raisins (or dates). Turn into a well-greased 10-inch angel food pan or 9-inch Bundt pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for one hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool.
If desired, add vanilla glaze of choice.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook rice; drain
well.
Cut
marshmallows fine and mix all ingredients together,
folding
in the whipped cream last. Let stand in the refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown meats and completely drain well.
Combine cooked and drained meats, soup, tomatoes and cheese in crock-pot.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Dip can be made hotter by using hot sausage or Mexican Velveeta cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake as directed on box.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of the cake batter into the pan.
Bake until done, about 15 minutes, at 350°.

title: rice and tomato soup
directions: Cook rice with water, onion, chicken cubes or powder, condiments until done.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Serve with saltines.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on tray.
Cover with salsa.
Mix chopped veggies.
Layer and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Cook onion, garlic and chili powder in 2 tablespoons oil in large saucepan until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, cumin, oregano, salt and pepper.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Mix together cheeses.
Heat oil in skillet.
Dip each tortilla lightly in hot oil; drain.
Dip tortilla in tomato sauce.
Put 2 tablespoons cheese on each tortilla and roll up.
Place seam side down in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour on tomato sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top each serving with lettuce and black olives.
Serve with sour cream or plain yogurt.
!Muy bueno!

title: great pumpkin pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Add boiling water.
Put mixture into blender with rest of ingredients.
Blend until frothy.
Let stand until slightly thickened before pouring into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: sprouts and apple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in 4-quart salad bowl.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: For the crust:
Combine 1 cup sugar, egg and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift the flour and baking powder; blend in with the sugar and egg mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 45 minutes (the cooler the better) and press into a 14-inch round pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool before filling.

title: sugar-free cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
To serve:
Stir 4 tablespoons into 1 cup boiling water.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together apples, cranberries and white sugar and place in baking dish.
Mix together well oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, nuts and margarine.
Sprinkle over cranberry mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and place in large bowl.
Open 1 can biscuits and cut in quarters.
Place in bowl and stir or shake to cover.
Place coated pieces in lightly greased Bundt pan or loaf.
Melt margarine, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in microwave.
Pour half over first can of biscuits.

title: raspberry brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a 1-quart glass bowl, microwave chocolate chips on High power 1 1/2 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Set aside; let cool to room temperature.

title: edna's coke cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour a Bundt cake pan.
In a mixing bowl, put cake mix, instant pudding, 4 eggs, oil and Coke.
Blend for 3 minutes or until batter is smooth.
Add lemon flavor.
Put in pan and bake for 45 minutes. Use toothpick to test for doneness.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cook chocolate pudding according to directions on package; stir in the egg.
Mix with Jiffy cake mix and melted margarine.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Sprinkle the top with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ranch style carrot salad
directions: Whisk dressing mix, mayonnaise, sour cream and honey in a bowl.
Add carrots and toss.
Serve chilled.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion for 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, sour cream and carrots; add squash and onion.
Melt butter and mix with seasoning and place 1/2 in baking dish with vegetables.
Place the other 1/2 of seasoning on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: moldavian potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool until manageable and cut in 3/4-inch cubes.
Pour garlic and olive oil on potatoes. Toss and let come to room temperature.
Add Feta and scallions and toss.
Sprinkle on vinegar (more to taste, if desired), dill, salt and pepper.
Let sit at least 1 hour on counter to let flavors settle.
Serves 4.

title: butterscotch clusters
directions: Melt butterscotch in top of double boiler.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: baked chicken and vegetables(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place vegetables in a small baking dish; sprinkle with 1/2 package soup.
Place chicken on top of vegetables; sprinkle with remaining soup and cover with foil. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: 3 month salad
directions: Sprinkle salt over cabbage and cover with water.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain.
Mix together with cabbage 1 bunch of celery, cut fine and 3 green peppers cut fine.

title: choc-nut cake
directions: Chop most of cherries in half.
Then chop the nuts and biscuits until they are pea size.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add chocolate, then sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat. Fold in egg yolk and brandy.
Beat in egg white.
Add the cherries, walnuts and biscuits (not the crumbs).
Press into loaf pan and cool in refrigerator.

title: stilton leek soup
directions: Cook leek, garlic, celery, carrot, bay leaf and thyme for 5 minutes in butter.
Add potatoes and broth; cook until tender. Discard bay leaf.
Put through blender.
Stir in half and half and heat.
Whisk in cheese until smooth.
Add Port and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with chives as garish.
Do not boil.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Combine noodles, tuna fish, mushroom soup, salt, onion, pimiento and milk.
Mix lightly with a fork until well blended. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: da best bean soup
directions: Sort and wash 2 cups bean mix.
Soak beans overnight in water. Drain beans and add 2 quarts fresh water, ham, onion, garlic, salt and and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: paradise spinach rice salad
directions: Combine orange juice, dressing, honey and orange peel.
Stir into chilled rice.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients before serving.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add corn, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over top and mix well.
Add whipping cream.
Cook until thickened while stirring.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 300° about 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat
until creamy.
Add vanilla, flour and salt. Beat until mix is blended.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast bran muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add liquids and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
(Batter will keep up to 6 weeks in fridge.)
Makes 4 to 6 dozen.

title: chocolate-pecan brownies
directions: To make Chocolate-Peanut Butter Brownies, add 1/2 cup peanut butter (and omit pecans, optional).

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Prepare spaghetti noodles as directed on box.
Pour McCormick salad dressing mix over spaghetti noodles.
Let stand 1 hour. Pour Italian dressing over spaghetti, adding peppers, onions, tomatoes and celery.

title: creamy tortellini party pick-ups
directions: Add tortellini to saucepan of boiling water.
Boil, uncovered, 15 minutes until tender.
Drain.
Heat butter in pan.
Stir in garlic.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in cream, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tortellini to pan and mix well. Cool tortellini 5 minutes, then thread 2 on each toothpick.
Serve warm.

title: sister agnes' caramel corn
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Bring to boil; stir over medium-high heat. Stir rapidly to hard ball stage, 260°, for about 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda quickly but thoroughly. Pour at once over popcorn in large roasting pan.
Stir gently until all kernels are coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter into iron skillet. Add sugar mixture and mix lightly.
Combine beaten egg yolks and milk.
Add to mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie crust. Cover with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Brown in oven for 15 minutes at 300°.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Combine onion, sour cream and sauerkraut.
Spread on bottom of 11 x 13 inch casserole.
Top with thinly sliced corned beef. Layer shredded swiss cheese on top of corned beef.
Chop bread into cubes and coat with melted butter.
Place bread on top of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another 10 to 15 minutes to brown top.

title: hawaiian yum yum cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in two 8-inch pans or 45 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan. Check with toothpick until it comes out clean.
Cool.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Wash apples; do not peel.
Cut in quarters and remove core. Cook apples and cider slowly in a heavy kettle until done.
Put through a food mill or sieve.
Measure sieved fruit.
Place in crock-pot.
Add 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon allspice and 1/2 teaspoon cloves for each pint of fruit.
Mix well.
Cover crock-pot.
Cook on high for 6 to 8 hours.
Stir about every 2 hours.
After 3 hours, remove cover so that fruit will cook down.
Place in hot sterilized jars.
Process to seal. Makes approximately 5 pints.

title: baked potato cheese and chive soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in
margarine until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly. Gradually stir in chicken broth and milk. Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Add potatoes, Worcestershire sauce and dry mustard.
Stir gently.

title: tang pies
directions: Mix together. Can use mixer. Pour into pie shells and refrigerate. Makes 2 pies.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Place half of apples in pastry-lined pan. Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt together. Sprinkle half the sugar mixture over apples. Add rest of apples, then dot with butter and top with remaining sugar mixture. Cover with top crust. If apples are real juicy, add 1 or 2 tablespoons flour to sugar mixture. Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sparkling fruit
directions: Slice peaches into bowl.
Top with other fruit.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, slice bananas into fruit mixture.
Pour catawaba over fruit and serve. Makes 10 portions.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture. Add eggs, alternating, beating after each.
Add vanilla, chopped nuts, apples and coconut.
Put into greased pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool in pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: white wine sauce
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add salt and pepper; add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 tablespoons hot sauce to the cold beaten egg yolk, then return this to the hot mixture.
Stir briskly.
Add wine and also stir briskly.

title: ice cream jello
directions: Drain can of fruit.
In a blender, combine boiling water and Jell-O.
Add ice cream while blending slowly.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add fruit and stir in.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put tortillas in bottom of pan. Put chicken over tortillas.
Add onion and bell pepper, soups (mixed together), Ro-Tel tomatoes and juice from cans.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.

title: 3 pan red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk.
Add eggs, oil, flavor, soda and vinegar, mix and then add food coloring.
Bake at 350°. After cake cools, add frosting.

title: sweet and sour hamburger
directions: Combine crumbs, chopped onion, the seasonings and 1/2 cup water.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then mix lightly into hamburger. Shape into 4 patties.
Brown in small amount of fat (or oil). Cover with sliced onions.
Combine brown sugar, flour, vinegar, 2 tablespoons water and mustard.
Pour over meat patties.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes on low heat.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In a deep saucepan, first pour the oil then add the flour, firmly pressing the flour into the oil until the flour turns brown. Add water and mix until it thickens. If it is too thick continue to add water until it is as thick as you like. Add chili powder, garlic powder, cumin and salt. Taste to see if you need to add any more of these ingredients to your desire.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook in enough water to cover.
Saute large chopped onion in butter or bacon drippings.
Add milk to cooked potatoes, sauteed onion, salt and pepper.
Butter to taste. May be thickened with cold water and cornstarch blended together. Top with bacon crumbs, if desired, before stirring.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut, then slice top from each pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes and rinse.
Cook peppers in enough boiling water to cover for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except almonds.
Put in lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature; whip until fluffy. Gradually add Eagle Brand, while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish top of pie with cherry pie filling.

title: pam's date cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, brown sugar and 1/2 cup granulated sugar. Mix in eggs and cream well.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Roll out like jelly roll.

title: special french dressing
directions: Mix in order given and beat thoroughly.
Pour in a jar and store in fridge.
Can be mixed in shaker instead of beating.
Shake until mixed and thick.
Shake everytime you use.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Skin and sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine milk, soup and gravy mix in medium bowl.
Coat chicken with soup mixture.
Place chicken in crock-pot.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cook on high for 4 hours and cook on low another 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and eggs and stir.
Fold in coconut and vinegar.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop creole
directions: Brown pork chops on each side and place in a casserole dish. Place a bell pepper ring on top of each chop and an onion ring on top of each pepper.
Pour rice over all, keeping as level as possible.
Put sliced tomato on rice.
Pour consomme over all. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: best ever chocolate pie(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a microwave-safe mixing bowl. Stir in milk, chocolate syrup and egg yolks.
Microwave at Medium (50%) for 8 to 10 minutes or until thick, stirring every two minutes with a wire whisk.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts.
Pour into crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Stir powdered sugar into Cool Whip.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with cocoa.

title: hot mulled punch
directions: Pour fruit juices into a 30 to 36-cup coffee maker.
Place remaining ingredients in basket.
Put in coffee maker and perk. Upon completion of perking cycle, remove basket.
Serve hot. Makes 40 punch cup servings.

title: arizona style beans
directions: Soak beans in water.
Cook at low temperature until tender. Add salt, garlic salt, chili powder, chopped onion, pepper and beef.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add sauce and bouillon.
Heat.
Serve.

title: northern pike
directions: Place scaled but unskinned fish in shallow baking pan.
Salt the cavity.
In separate skillet, saute onion, green pepper and celery.
Add tomatoes, mashed slightly, and simmer until well blended.
Pour mixture over fish, scooping spoonfuls into cavity. Bake in moderate oven, basting occasionally.
Fish is thoroughly baked when gently poked with fork tine, it does not weep.
Serve with baked potatoes, slice of lemon and salad.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until lemon color.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Heat the milk and stick of oleo until very hot and add to cake mixture.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Bring to a boil.
Let stand until cool.
Pour over beans, onions and green pepper.
Better if salad stands overnight.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together in a large bowl by hand all ingredients.
Ready to serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Chill, then add all ingredients.
Amount of mayonnaise is to your own taste.

title: refrigerator bran muffins(this recipe can be made and stored in fridge 4 to 6 weeks)
directions: Step 1:
Put boiling water over bran cereals and set aside to cool.

title: eggs florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook spinach in medium saucepan over low heat. Drain well. Place hot spinach in greased pan. Make a depression for each egg in spinach. Break 1 egg in each depression. Prepare Cheese Sauce. Pour over eggs and spinach. Bake 35 minutes or until done.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Pat dressing on top of steak.
Roll up in a roll and close either with string or toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Add a jar of homestyle gravy.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine the first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Combine next 3 ingredients and add to creamed mixture until well blended.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonful 3 inches apart.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie (cookie will appear moist; do not overbake), 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookie.
Let cookies cool for 2 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, 2 egg yolks, milk, vanilla, butter and cocoa until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites while adding 1/3 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff.
Bake in 350° oven until top is browned.

title: mother's 1-2-3 pie
directions: Mix and pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: pat's dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly.
Then slice 1/3-inch thick.
Pack into sterilized quart jars.
Place 1/2 teaspoon each of mustard seed, celery seed and pickling spices in each jar.
Place 1 whole bay leaf, 1 clove of garlic and 1 sprig of fresh dill in each jar.

title: peanut butter pie(dietetic)
directions: With mixer, blend peanut butter into milk.
Add pudding, beating until it starts to thicken. Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: canned fish
directions: Soak fish in water with 1/2 pound salt for one hour.
Put fish in pint jars with a mixture of 1/2 teaspoon salt, vinegar and catsup.
Pressure cook at 10, boil for 100 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with paprika and more cheese, if desired.

title: oriental kabobs
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Mix soy sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and garlic powder.
Place chicken, green peppers, mushrooms and tomatoes in bowl.
Add marinade and let stand one hour.
Arrange on small skewers.
Place on roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Brush with marinade.
Cook 10 minutes. Turn, brush again and cook 10 additional minutes.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Beat cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Prepare toppings with 1 cup milk and vanilla. Add 1/2 of topping.
Mix to cheese mix and spoon into crust. Spread other 1/2 of topping on pie.
Garnish with roasted peanuts and chill 5 hours.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir the first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Place chocolate kiss or star in middle of each ball and press down.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar milk, margarine and salt to hard boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: florida lime pie
directions: Whisk condensed milk, lime juice, lime peel and egg yolks to blend.
Tint with green food coloring, if you want.
Whip egg whites to stiff peaks.
Gently fold into lime mixture.
Pour into crust and smooth top.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done; debone and dice.
Using 1/4 to 1/2 of chicken broth, saute onion and mushrooms in the broth and butter.
When onion is golden brown, add soups and mix well.
Add diced chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth left from cooking chicken.
Mix and serve in a casserole dish; top with cheese.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar.
Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add to yeast mixture and keep in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Shape into rolls and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts into a deep pan of water with bouillon cubes, carrot and celery.
Cook until tender, cool, debone and cut chicken into pieces.

title: swiss cheese pie
directions: Line deep pie plate with 9-inch pie crust.
Grate 1/2 pound Swiss cheese. Dredge cheese with 1 tablespoon flour.
Spread cheese evenly on pie crust.
Mix eggs with milk and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve hot.
For variety, you can add crumbled bacon, minced precooked chicken or very finely chopped precooked vegetables to cheese pie.

title: low-fat vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onion in the margarine, stirring to separate and coat. (Can be done in microwave for 2 minutes, then stir and continue for 2 more minutes.)
Let onions cool.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, Egg Scramblers, bacon bits and chives.
Pour into a 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes; take out and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven for 15 more minutes, or until pie begins to brown and a knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mock chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Cook about 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hawaiian punch cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool; punch holes in top. Boil sugar and pineapple with juice, then pour over cake.
Mix the pudding with milk.
Add coconut.
Chill slightly.
Pour over pineapple topping; let cool.
Cover with whipped topping; top with nuts.

title: weight watcher's strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and water together.
Heat over medium heat until thick. Remove from heat and mix in Sweet 'N Low and Jell-O. Put strawberries in pie shell and then pour mixture over the strawberries. Refrigerate until firm.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Drain the
peas and dice the eggs.
Add all ingredients together with the mayonnaise.
Toss lightly.
Serve on lettuce and top with croutons.

title: salted-in-the-shell shrimp
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Toss the shrimp with the oil and sprinkle with the pepper.
Spread 1/4-inch of salt in a large baking dish.
Put the shrimp on the salt and turn them once or twice so that they are lightly coated.
Bake the shrimp until they are cooked through, about 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt the butter. Squeeze 1 tablespoon juice from the lemon and stir into butter as dipping sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cantonese egg rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except peanut oil).
Put in egg roll wrappers.
Deep fry 3 to 5 minutes until browned and crispy.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, drain.
Lightly cook noodles. Mix spinach, mozzarella, cottage cheese, sour cream and eggs. Layer noodles, hamburger, cheese mixtures and spaghetti sauce. End with cheese on top.
Needs to be put in a deep 13x15 pan. Bake at 375° 1 1/2 hours until it has boiled good and not too juicy.
Let cool 15 minutes.

title: italian sauce
directions: Pour in a bowl Heinz ketchup and warm water.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix.
Add oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Cook over a low heat for 3 minutes, then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.

title: layer cookies
directions: Use 3 pans 10 1/2 x 7 x 1 1/4-inches.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook hamburger and onions until brown.
Drain off liquid.
Add soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into ovenproof baking dish. Top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rump roast supreme
directions: Place meat on rack in Dutch oven.
Combine mushroom mix, apricots and salt and spread over meat.
Cover tightly and cook at 325° for 2 hours.
Add onion and lemon juice to cooking liquid and continue cooking, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Remove meat to warm platter.
If thicker gravy is desired, combine water and flour to thicken liquid.
Add snipped parsley and cook 3 to 4 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat milk, butter, sugar and salt until warm and butter is almost melted.
Combine 2 1/4 cups of flour in a large bowl with yeast.
Add warm milk to flour mixture.
Add eggs and beat with mixer on high for 3 minutes.
Using a wooden spoon, stir as much of the remaining 2 1/4 to 2 3/4 cups of flour into dough mixture as you can.
Put rest of flour on board.
Turn dough into floured surface.
Knead until dough is smooth and elastic (3 to 5 minutes).
Shape into ball; put into greased bowl, turning once. Let rise 1 hour until doubled.
Punch down.
Put on floured surface.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Roll dough out.

title: chocolate on chocolate cake
directions: Heat butter, cocoa, oil and water together in saucepan until butter is melted.
Sift flour, soda and sugar together into large bowl.
Pour heated liquid over dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Add eggs; mix well.
Then add buttermilk; mix until blended.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine the evaporated milk, condensed milk, sugar, vanilla extract, butter and slightly beaten egg yolks in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Add the coconut and pecans.
Cool until thickened enough to spread, beating occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: lemon meringue pie(foods lab special)
directions: Bake pie shell.
Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir at least half of the hot mixture gradually into egg yolks.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, lemon peel, lemon juice and food color.
Pour into pie shell.

title: graham cracker cookies(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Divide each graham cracker square into 4 pieces.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Line bottom of cookie sheet with cracker pieces.
Cook margarine, butter and sugar.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes. Pour over cracker pieces.
Cover with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take up each square from pan while hot.
Cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: bechamel sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy-bottomed saucepan.
Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes a thick bubbly paste, but do not let it brown.
Add milk, stirring constantly as sauce thickens.
Bring to a low boil and season with salt and pepper. Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes more, again stirring constantly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream the sugar, eggs and shortening; then add the rest of the mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: plain scones
directions: Sieve the flour, salt and baking powder.
Rub in butter.
Mix to a light dough with milk.
Roll out on a floured board and cut with round or fancy cutter.
Bake in a hot oven at 400°.

title: tomato pie(side dish with steak, chicken, etc.)
directions: Combine Bisquick and milk.
Pat into 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Top with tomatoes, onion, chives, blended season, basil and lemon pepper.
Grate Cheddar cheese and mix with mayonnaise.
Spread over top of tomatoes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: noodle rice pilaf
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter. Add the rice and noodles. Cook and stir until lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Stir in broth. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until broth is absorbed and rice is tender. Stir in parsley. Yield: 4 servings.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Saute onions in oil until tender and put into pie shell.
Mix remaining ingredients, except cheese, and pour over onions.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and shape into rolls.
Put in foil (shiny side next to meat) and refrigerate for 24 hours. Punch holes in foil and place rolls on rack in shallow pan with water under rack.
Bake 90 minutes at 325°.
Makes 3 or 4 rolls.

title: velvet walnut fudge cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup walnuts on bottom of well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside remaining walnuts and chocolate chips. Measure remaining ingredients into mixing bowl.
Blend.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips and remaining walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Finish cooling on rack.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: layer salad
directions: Place in glass bowl.
Layer, starting with chopped lettuce, sliced cucumber, chopped green onions, tiny peas, egg slices, chopped celery, crumbled crisp bacon and then seal with Hellmann's mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with cheese over top.
Seal with Saran Wrap. Let set in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: christmas holly
directions: Tip:
Use butter on your fingers to prevent sticking.

title: cocktail sausages
directions: Bake sausage for 20 minutes on low heat (325°).
Mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Place sauce and sausage together in pan on low heat to keep warm.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Spread in layers the following:
pineapple, berries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over dish.
Mix melted margarine, pecans and 1/4 cup sugar and spread over top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbles appear all around sides and in middle of dish. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: oatmeal brownies
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese souffle(serves 4)
directions: Make a white sauce of the oil, margarine, milk and salt.
When cool, add the cheese and the egg yolk.
Beat egg whites in clean bowl and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese and rice
directions: Drain
mushrooms;
reserve liquid.
Lightly brown mushrooms, onions
and
almonds
in butter.
Add rice, parsley and cheese; mix
well.
Place
mixture in dish; add salt and meat extract mixed
with
water and mushroom liquid by pouring over rice. Cover and bake in 375° oven 1 hour.

title: best-ever pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well.
Add flavorings and mix.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
May be glazed while hot with a mixture of 1 cup powdered sugar and 3 tablespoons frozen orange juice.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix rice, soup, broccoli and onion. Cook 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove and place Cheez Whiz on top and place back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: salmon dip
directions: Remove bones and skin from salmon.
Place salmon on shallow platter.
Break up into chunky pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over salmon.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix well and pour over shredded cabbage.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and taco seasoning.
Spread on large dish or plate.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Doritos.

title: edible dirt
directions: Cream oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add pudding plus milk and Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos.
Alternate layers of filling and then Oreos, starting with filling and ending with Oreos. Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in large soup pot.
Add onions and wilt over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
Add sugar; turn heat to medium-low.
Cook, uncovered, until caramelized, 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add remaining liquid ingredients and cook, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Divide into ovenproof serving bowls.
Place slice of bread in each bowl.
Sprinkle cheese on top and broil until cheese is melted and brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the strawberry gelatin dessert with sugar in a small bowl. Heat 3/4 cup water in a saucepan until very hot.
Pour water over gelatin and sugar.
Stir with wooden spoon to dissolve it.
Put the bowl into refrigerator about 20 minutes so gelatin will be thickened, but not set.
Fold Cool Whip into gelatin.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine very warm water and yeast.
Melt margarine and beat with sugar in large bowl.
Add beaten egg.
Add dissolved yeast and flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight bowl and refrigerate; some rise will come.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, oil and lemon rind until creamy.
Add extract and dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix sour cream and soup together until smooth.
Pour mixture evenly over chicken.
Mix melted margarine, crumbled crackers and poppy seed.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. In a Pyrex dish, layer macaroni, cheese, margarine and crumbled crackers. Keep layering until all is used up. Top with crumbled crackers. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbling. Salt and
pepper to taste.

title: shrimp with pea pods stir-fry
directions: Mix cornstarch and ginger.
Blend in soy, sherry and broth. Set aside.
Place wok over high heat.
When wok is hot, add oil. When oil is hot, add garlic and shrimp.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add peas and stir-fry for about 2 minutes if fresh or 30 seconds if frozen.
Add water chestnuts and green onions.
Stir to mix.
Add cornstarch mixture and stir until it boils and thickens (about 1 minute).

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Cook first four ingredients together.
Cook to a soft ball forms.
Take off heat; add marshmallow cream fluffed and nuts if desired.

title: play clay ornaments
directions: Stir together dry ingredients in saucepan.
Add water and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is the consistency of moist mashed potatoes.
Turn out on a plate and cover with a damp cloth until cool enough to handle.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut shapes with cookie cutters.
Press hole near top of each ornament to dry on flat surface and harden overnight.
Paint, decorate and protect with a shiny glaze.

title: garden patch soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in 5-quart pot.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello to boiling.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Then add Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Refrigerate.

title: vanilla sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition. The dough will be very stiff; blend last flour by hand.
Do not chill dough.
Divide into two balls.
On a floured surface, roll each ball in a circle approximately 12 inches in diameter and 1/8-inch thick.
Dip cutters in flour before each use.
Bake cookies on ungreased cookie sheet on top rack of oven for 6 to 7 minutes, or until cookies are lightly browned.
Remove cookies from sheet immediately.
Yields 20 large cookies (4 inches to 5 1/2 inches).

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Pour cake mix into ungreased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla in bowl until creamy.
Pour cheese mix over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: almond delight
directions: Mix oleo, flour, nuts, sugar and coconut together in a long, shallow pan and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown, stirring every 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix milk and pudding mix together; beat 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread half of the nuts over flour mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add pudding mix over crumbs.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and refrigerate.

title: dewberry pie
directions: Bake at 350° to 375° until brown.

title: beef 'n wine over rice
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, allspice and wine. Cook 2 hours at 325°.
When meat is tender, add evaporated milk to make gravy.
Cook 1/2 hour more. Serve over rice.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Put in baking dish.
Mix soy sauce and water.
Pour over meat and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Heat oil in large skillet; cook meat 15 minutes.
While the meat is cooking, chop vegetables and add remaining ingredients; mix together.
Add vegetables to meat and cook 15 more minutes, stirring often.

title: holiday cider
directions: Wrap whole cloves, allspice and cinnamon in cheesecloth. Simmer in crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours.
Add water if it evaporates too much.

title: low-fat potato leek soup
directions: In soup pot, slowly boil potatoes, leeks, carrots and pepper to taste in 1 quart of water for 45 minutes.
Melt margarine in a skillet over low heat.
Add flour and stir until browned, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and gradually whisk in 1 cup of soup liquid.
Return flour mixture to soup and season with paprika. Bring to a boil and serve hot.
Serves 6. Contains 5 saturated fat calories.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well. Combine eggs and milk; stir well. Dip filets in egg mixture; dredge in flour mixture. Arrange on greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Drizzle with margarine. Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Bake in 8-inch round cake pan.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt together; let cool.
Mix with 8 or 12 ounces Cool Whip. Put in pie crust (regular or graham cracker).

title: caramels
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
In it, combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and 1/2 cup of the cream.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Slowly stir in the remaining 1/2 cup of cream.
Cook over low heat to medium ball stage, stirring almost constantly.
Remove from heat; add nuts and vanilla.
Pour in the buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Mark into 32 squares, when partially cool.
When cold, cut and wrap.
Store in an airtight container.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla. Gradually add flour and crushed potato chips until blended.
Form in rolls and roll on waxed paper. Slice and bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in greased 8 or 10-inch skillet for 25 to 30 minutes at 450°.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix with cream cheese.
Let cool and then add other ingredients.

title: cheesy pita triangles(yields 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Combine the cream cheese, butter and Parmesan cheese in a food processor and beat until very smooth.
Cut 4 of the tomatoes into thin strips; set aside.
Whirl the remaining tomatoes, oil and 1/2 cup of the cream cheese mixture in a blender until all smoothly pureed.
Combine the tomato puree with the cream cheese mixture and beat to blend.
Cover and chill for about 20 minutes or until firm.

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 20-25 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and granulated sugar at medium speed with electric mixer until mixture is creamy.
Chop 8 candy bars finely, fold into cream mixture and chopped candy bars into whipped topping.
Spread between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Chop remaining 2 candy bars.
Sprinkle on top.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and make into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: seafood quiche
directions: *Can substitute 1 pint half and half for cream and milk.

title: baked ham
directions: Place pineapple rings and cherries on ham, fastening with wooden picks.
Put ham in a baking pan and pour ginger ale over it. Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.
Baste every 1/2 hour with juice from the pan.

title: ann's hot taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Mix taco seasoning in meat. Put into large salad bowl.
Add cilantro, onion, lettuce, jalapenos and black olives.
Toss well.
Refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Take out of refrigerator and add cheese and tortillas. Mix again.
Top it off with taco salsa.

title: sugar cookies(christmas, valentine, etc.)
directions: Cream together eggs, butter and sugar. Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Add flavorings to creamed mixture.

title: pork chops with green peppers and pineapple
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Season with garlic salt.
Add green peppers, pineapple and soy sauce.
Cover; cook over low heat for 15 minutes, or until peppers are tender and pork chops are done. Serve with white rice.

title: tiny timmies
directions: Strain pineapple, saving syrup.
Cream butter and brown sugar. Add egg.
Measure our 3 Tbsp of the pineapple syrup and whip into butter mixture until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients; stir slowly until well bel ended.
Add crushed pineapple, butterscotch bits and nuts.
Mix well.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet and put a cherry in the middle of each cookie.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will be very soft when finished; remove from cookie sheet very carefully.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: celery relish
directions: Bring tomatoes to a boil and pour over the vegetables; let stand 10 minutes and drain.
Meanwhile, boil brown sugar, vinegar, mustard seeds and turmeric.
Pour this over drained vegetables; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into prepared jars, which have been tempered so as not to crack from hot liquid.
Can use empty mayo jars or whatever.
Tighten lids and invert until cool.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.
Whatever you do, do not give away; may be kept in refrigerator for up to 1 year, if it lasts that long, as it is delicious.

title: butternut and bacon soup
directions: Peel squash; cut into chunks.
Place in soup kettle with ham bone or ham.
Add chicken broth and water to cover.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, until squash is tender.

title: crystal pickles
directions: Slice dill pickles in thin slices into quart jar or slightly larger.
Measure sugar on top of sliced pickles.
Pour vinegar over pickles and sugar (do not stir; pickles make own juice syrup).
Put spices in cheesecloth and put in with pickles.
Cover and set in a cool place (can use refrigerator). Ready to use in a week to 10 days.

title: sweet 'n easy glaze
directions: Stir ingredients together with a small whisk until smooth and of a good drizzling consistency.
Drizzle over cooled cake. Yields glaze for one cake.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Then add carrots.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° to 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fyrst kake(almond tart)
directions: Mix flour and powdered sugar. Add softened butter. Add egg yolks and milk. Add sifted flour and baking powder. Form round ball. Don't work dough too hard.
Put in cool place approximately 1 hour.

title: brandy balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Beat well at med. speed.
Add egg yolk.	Mix well.
Combine flour and salt and gradually add to creamed mixture, alternately adding brandy. Beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in pecans.
Chill dough. Roll dough into 1 inch balls and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Cool.	Roll in powdered sugar.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bake the pie crust and let cool.
(I use Pillsbury pie crust from the dairy section.)
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water. Cook until thick and clear.
(Usually a full rolling boil.) Remove from heat and add jello and vanilla flavoring.
Let pie filling cool.
The cooler the filling the thicker it gets.	Layer the pie crust with sliced peaches.	Pour cool filling over fruit. Add more fruit and filling until crust is full.
Top with Cool Whip.
You can substitute strawberries and strawberry jello for strawberry pie.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat well and mix in flour, cocoa, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and mushrooms in butter. Place chicken and broccoli in greased 2-quart casserole. In a bowl, mix soup, milk, lemon juice and seasonings. Spoon evenly over chicken and broccoli. If using stuffing mix, toss with melted butter and spread or sprinkle evenly over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly and top is brown. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: froot loop cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt chocolate.
Mix well and spoon out.

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine onion and cucumbers in a large bowl. In a separate bowl combine the remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour over cucumbers and onions. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: camping eggs
directions: Place hash in large frypan.
Brown lightly.
Place eggs over hash.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook to desired egg doneness.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick vegetable spray.
Mix together pecans and coconut.
Spread in bottom of pan and set aside.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 12 x 8 x 3-inch pan.

title: christine's champagne punch
directions: Combine all in large punch bowl.
Mix gently, serve and enjoy. Serves 28 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grind crackers into crumbs.
Melt margarine and mix in crumbs. Put small part of crumbs in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then, mix chicken with soup and sour cream.
Put a layer of chicken mixture on top of crumbs.
Add more crumbs on top, then chicken, etc., finishing with crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This makes a lot.
It can be halved.

title: frozen champagne salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Then add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan, or one a little smaller.
Cover and freeze.

title: sweet potato pudding(russia)
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Grease a 2 quart baking dish. Beat eggs, add molasses(honey), melted butter and salt. Stir in grated sweet potatoes. Pour into baking dish. Bake for 2 hours or until the pudding is a dark caramel color. Be sure to grate the sweet potatoes just before using them so they will not turn dark, the dish may not look appetizing if sweet potatoes are grated very long. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: Cover chicken with water in boiler and cook over medium heat until done.
Remove skin and debone.
Save broth in pot.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Cook rest of vegetables in 2 cups water for 10 minutes or until soft.
Add cooked onion, corn, milk and butter.
Add seasonings with salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 cups of soup.
This can be frozen.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with Crisco.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake for 10 more minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove from sheet to cool.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: hoppin john
directions: Cook rice.
Saute onion, scallions and celery in bacon fat. Toss with crumbled bacon and the hot rice.
Serve immediately.

title: rita's cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add pineapple and other ingredients. Form in ball and roll in about 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: zesty wild rice
directions: Mix everything in bowl. Toss with dressing. Chill for 1 hour.

title: egg in a nest
directions: Lay slice of bread flat and cut a circle in the middle with a glass.
Add butter to heated skillet.
When melted, lay bread in skillet.
Break egg in center.
When fried, flip bread and egg (toast circle).
Cook until desired hardness.
Season as desired.

title: summer light cheese cake(dietetic)
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl and freeze until crystals begin to form, then whip.
Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup, then heat to boiling.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling pineapple juice.
Allow to cool until thick, but not set.
Add cheese, sweetener and flavorings; beat well.
Fold in pineapple.
Fold in whipped milk. Line a 9 x 12-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs and fill with mixture.
Chill.
Yield:
12 servings (3 x 3-inch servings). Calories:
124 per serving.

title: banana and date salad
directions: Prepare bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add whipped cream and blend.
Chill thoroughly; place in serving dishes. Stuff one nut in each date and place on top of bananas.
Garnish with coconut and serve chilled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir well.
Add 1 cup mixed juice drained from apricots and pineapple.
Refrigerate jello until it starts to jell.
Mix in drained apricots, chopped into small pieces and drained pineapple.
Add 1 cup (or more) small marshmallows.
Let set until firm.
Mix topping and spread over jello.

title: pie crust
directions: Put shortening, milk and boiling water together, mix well.
Add sifted flour and salt, blend together until ready for rolling out on floured surface.
This is a no fail pie crust and is nice and flaky.
Will make a double crust.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring 3 minutes. Add frozen strawberries and stir constantly until berries separate and gelatin begins to thicken. Blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth.
Chill if necessary until mixture mounds. Spoon into pie crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add bananas.
Add condensed milk, evaporated milk and cream.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze. Makes 2 quarts.

title: "grandma cunningham's" home cooked dressing for head lettuce
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Remove from stove and blend in flour.
Add sugar, salt and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vinegar and water; mix well.
Bring mixture to a bubbling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and use hot for wilted lettuce or cold for crisp salad.

title: quick sugar-free cheese cake pie
directions: Mix milk with vanilla pudding mix.
Add cream cheese and lemon immediately after mixing pudding.
Blend together well and pour into pie shell quickly.
Put in refrigerator until chilled.

title: muffin pizza
directions: Open muffins.
Spread tomato sauce with salt and pepper in tomato sauce.
Add topping (whatever you like).
Put cheese on top. Cook until cheese is melted at 300° and voila!
A quick snack!

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press mixture into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Chill 6 hours before serving.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat in oil; season with salt and pepper.
Drain pineapple, reserving the liquid.
Add enough water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Stir liquid and barbecue sauce onto meat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.

title: hamburger helper
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Stir together.
Bring to boil.
Cook on medium-low for 20 minutes for rice and 10 minutes for macaroni.
Cover with lid and stir occasionally.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Stir cream cheese to soften, adding mayonnaise.
Fold in Cool Whip; add remaining ingredients.
Freeze.

title: tomato-corn chowder (soup)
directions: Cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Add potatoes, water and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add corn and tomato juice (I use soup).
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Add milk, sugar, cinnamon and salt to Grape-Nuts mixture.
Beat eggs until light.
Blend into pudding mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: delicious oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/4 cups boiling water
over
cup oatmeal.
Let set 20 minutes.
Cream 1/2 cup oleo and 1
cup
brown
sugar
well. Add 1 cup white sugar.
Add 2 unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each one.
Blend in oatmeal mixture.
Sift
1/2 cups
flour,
1 teaspoon nutmeg, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1
teaspoon soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
While cake is still hot, pour on topping
and put under broiler for 2 minutes or until browned.

title: shrimp salad mold
directions: Bring soup and water to boil; add cream cheese and stir. Dissolve gelatine; add to soup mix.
Whip and cool.
Add other ingredients; pour into mold.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Toss chicken and egg until all pieces are coated.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cornstarch over chicken; toss until all pieces are coated. Melt shortening in medium skillet.
Add chicken pieces; cook over medium heat until brown.
Remove chicken from skillet and set aside.

title: marcia's ice cream(5 quarts)
directions: Whip eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add condensed milk, evaporated milk and salt.
Add 1 can drained crushed pineapple.
Fill rest of freezer with whole milk.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Mix strawberry jello and 2 cups boiling water.	Add all of other ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour half of mixture into dish;
let	congeal.
Spread
sour	cream
over congealed mixture. Pour the remaining mixture over this.
Congeal.

title: fried okra and green tomatoes
directions: Combine okra, green tomatoes and onion. Add cornmeal and toss gently.
Pour oil to a depth of 2-inches into a large skillet. Heat to 375°.
Fry half of the mixture until golden brown. Remove with slotted spoon and drain. Repeat procedure. Sprinkle with salt and serve immediately.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Let rest until foamy.
In a large bowl, mix the flour and garlic salt.
Add olive oil to yeast mixture.
Make well in flour and add yeast mixture; stir to combine.
If too sticky, add more flour.
Knead on a floured board until smooth and elastic, adding flour as needed. Pat dough into ball.
Put in large bowl and set in a warm place covered with a clean towel for about 1 hour or until doubled in size.
Punch down dough and divide into 2 equal portions.
Roll out on a floured surface into a 12-inch circle.
Place on pan and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 2 (12-inch) pizzas.
Top with your sauce and toppings.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Salt and garlic to taste.
Add tomato sauce; cook on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and cream cheese; simmer on medium-low heat for 10 minutes.
(Have noodles cooked and drained.)
Mix noodles with meat mixture.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle cheese on top last 5 minutes.

title: canned tomato juice
directions: Cook tomatoes and salt.
Put through food Foley to remove skins and seeds.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Put in clean canning jars and seal.
Hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: rice and meat pies
directions: Cook together the hamburger, onions, salt and pepper. When browned, drain and add the rice.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 2/3 cup Carnation milk.
Pour 1/2 batter into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels with 1/2 cup Carnation milk.
Pour over cake.
Add 1 cup nuts and 1 cup chocolate chips.
Pour other half of batter over and sprinkle with chopped pecans and bake.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, walnuts and margarine together and spread evenly in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle 2/3 of the baked crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine egg whites, sugar, strawberries and lemon juice.
Beat at high speed to stiff peaks, about 10 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream, whipped.
Spoon over crumbs; top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.

title: chili barbecue beans
directions: Brown the ground chuck, onion, garlic and oil.
Add all seasonings.
Stir on low heat.
Add A.1. sauce, tomatoes, sauce and brown sugar.
Stir. Simmer with lid on for 15 minutes.
Add all your beans and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
You can add more spices or less, also more sugar or less, to your taste.

title: cream cheese and pepper jelly spread
directions: This makes 2 serving trays so on 2 trays form a ball about 5-inches wide from each container of cream cheese.
Form an opening in center of ball and spoon in jelly.
Then arrange crackers around the ball and serve.
For a more attractive look, use red jelly with wheat crackers in one and green jelly with vegetable crackers on the other.

title: pina colada fruit salad
directions: Combine coconut, yogurt, pineapple juice, rum extract and coconut cream in a small glass bowl.
Stir to blend.
Fold in fresh or canned fruits before serving.
Calories:
150; cholesterol:
14 mg; fat 2 grams; sodium 58 mg.

title: lasagne
directions: Repeat layers.
Put second layer of noodles across opposite the first layer.
End with American and Mozzarella cheese on top. Bake until noodles are tender.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and brown hamburger in skillet.
Pour in casserole.
Add cabbage when tender and soft.
Add soups and stir. Cover with a tight lid.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: taco pizza
directions: Roll out pizza crust (store bought is easier) in deep pizza or cake pan.
Spread out refried beans.
Cook at 425° until pizza crust is done.
Dice up your tomatoes and onions while pizza crust is baking.
Once the pizza crust is done, add your tomatoes, onion, lettuce and shredded cheese (these will not be baked).
Top off with your salsa.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Microwave butter in medium micro-proof bowl at High (100%) for 45 to 60 seconds or until melted. Add cocoa; blend well. Beat in sugar, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts. Refrigerate at least 8 hours or until firm. May be chilled overnight.

title: snicker pie
directions: Spray pan with pam.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in freezer.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, Parmesan and butter in saucepan. Add garlic powder and pepper to taste.
Heat to boiling.
Add more milk if mixture is too thick.
Consistency should be like a sauce. Reduce heat to simmer while noodles are boiling.
Pour Alfredo Sauce over cooked noodles.
Add chicken and/or broccoli if desired.

title: "not fired" rice
directions: Coat wok or large skillet with Pam.
Add oil, coating sides. Put over medium heat until hot.
Add celery, carrots, onion, ginger and garlic; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and bamboo shoots; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Stir in cooked rice until heated. Push rice mix to sides, forming a well in center.
Add remaining 1 teaspoon oil.
Pour egg into well and cook until set, stirring. Stir rice mix into egg.
Add soy sauce and sherry, stirring constantly.
When ready to serve, garnish with green onions. Yields 5 cups/about 107 calories per 1/2 cup serving/fat 2.5 gr.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix milk, flour and margarine.
Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 400° until brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: herb bread
directions: Place rolled oats, margarine, salt and boiling water in a bowl.
In the meantime, soften yeast in water with the 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
When water mixture has cooled to
a warm temperature, add yeast.
Add the whole wheat flour; add 2 cups of the white or bread flour.
Mix.
Add 2 more cups of white flour. Knead until smooth (5 to 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl. Cover.
Allow to rise in warm place until about double in size. Punch down and turn over.
Let rise another 30 minutes.
Shape into 2 or 3 loaves.
Let rise again until about double in size, about 45 minutes to one hour.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Bread is done when loaves sound hollow when tapped on top with fingers.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Drain kraut and place on bottom of dish. Sprinkle dressing on it.
Cover with pieces of corned beef. Spread cheese on this.
Put bread cubes on top of the cheese. Brush with melted butter.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Tasty!

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; gradually cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour, lemon juice and grated lemon rind and mix well.
Stir in milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in.
Pour mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf baking dish.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° for approximately 10 minutes to brown. Can also use individual custard cups.
Baking time might be slightly less.

title: caramel candy
directions: Mix together and boil sugar, Karo and 1 cup of whipping cream to 236° on candy thermometer.
Add 1 cup cream; boil to 236° again.
Add final cup of cream and boil to 240°.
Remove from heat.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla and 2 cups chopped pecans (optional).

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered pie plate (12 inches) or an oblong dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade biscuit mix
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until mix resembles coarse crumbs.
Store in covered airtight container for up to 6 weeks.

title: cranberry cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and walnuts together.
Press into spring-form pan.
