Spread 1 can whole cranberry sauce over crust.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and eggs well . Add flour, sour cream and vanilla; beat 2 minutes. Pour in pan over cranberry sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until firm to touch.
Turn off oven and leave slightly ajar to cool for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with can of whole cranberry sauce and cranberries.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown.

title: homecoming punch
directions: Combine sugar and 1 gallon of water in pan.
Heat until sugar dissolves.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit juices, 1 gallon of water and extract.
Let stand or freeze until ready to serve.
Pour 2 quarts over crushed ice and 1/2 quart of ginger ale.

title: potato soup
directions: In a soup pot, combine the first four ingredients with the water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add salt to taste. Simmer.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and place in deep dish and bake for 20 minutes at 350° or microwave until warm and bubbling.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Combine eggs, milk, pineapple, butter and sugar.
Add bread crumbs.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot or cold, with or without whipped cream.

title: mountain blueberry coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Beat eggs; add milk, then add to flour mixture.
Add blueberries.
Pour into two 9-inch greased round cake pans. Sprinkle coconut on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.

title: chicken salad on buns
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well. Spoon about 1/3 cup onto each roll. Wrap each tightly in foil. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and papaya slaw(low-cost, low-fat and low-calorie)
directions: Toss all ingredients in large serving bowl until blended.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Add water to reserve to equal 2 cups.
In saucepan, bring beets and liquid to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add cold water, onion, horseradish, vinegar and salt.
Chill until partially set. Stir in beets, celery and olives.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill.
Top with dollop of mayonnaise and sliced stuffed olives.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix condensed milk, cold milk and Cool Whip with pudding mix until blended.
Layer cookies and bananas.
Pour liquid mixture over layers.
Make 2 layers in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass dish.

title: chocolate nut cookies
directions: Mix together flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, cocoa, Crisco and baking powder like pie dough.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to dough mixture.
Roll into balls. Bake on greased pan at 375° until firm (like moist cake).
Dip in glaze made of powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.

title: chicken and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil until browned.
Add vegetables and stir until crisp-tender.
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, brown sugar, garlic powder and ginger.
Add to skillet.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy sunday chicken dish
directions: Grease baking dish.
Place ingredients in dish, cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 325° or bake 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
This will bake and be ready to serve when you return from church.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: crispy chicken thighs
directions: Soak thighs overnight in sauce.
Roll thighs in 1/2 cup flour and 1/2 cup cornstarch (mixed) and deep fry until golden brown.

title: the garnet (not gamecock garnet!) salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened, then fold in fruit and nuts. Pour into 1-quart mold; chill until firm.
Unmold.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: country breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain; set aside.
Mix cheese, peppers, onions, eggs and milk together.
Add sausage and pour mixture in 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top or knife inserted comes out clean.

title: taco pie
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Pour off grease.
Add taco sauce and simmer 5 minutes.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with unrolled crescent dinner rolls.
Push together with fingers where there are spaces between triangles and the top edges.
Points come together at center of pan.
Spread 1/2 cup crushed corn chips over crust. Spread meat mixture over chips.
Spread sour cream over meat. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of sour cream.
Top pie with 1/2 cup crushed corn chips and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: godmother's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Chop onion and garlic.
Add to meat; saute and add olive oil and salt.
Add tomato paste; mix well.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Crumble dried red peppers and add chili tepines.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup water; stir well.
Turn heat low and simmer all day.
Stir to avoid sticking.
Add small quantities of water throughout the cooking.

title: tadpoles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease an 8-inch pan. Put egg, corn (undrained) and 1/2 cup cheese in a bowl; mix well. Add dry muffin mix. Stir until mixed (batter will be thick). Pour into dish; arrange sausage links on top of batter. Bake for 30 minutes or until top is golden. Sprinkle on remaining cheese. Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Cut into squares.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Combine honey and peanut butter. Gradually work in dry milk and quick oats. Shape in balls.
Serve.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper, and garlic.
Combine eggs and buttermilk with a whisk.
Coat chops with flour.
Dip in egg mixture.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place in a single layer in a shallow oiled baking pan.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine over chops.
Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine and mix with all ingredients, except 1/4 cup margarine and corn flake crumbs.
Put in 2-quart casserole or square baking dish.
Grease dish first.
Melt remaining 1/4 cup margarine and mix with 2 cups corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order given.
Pour into 4 greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Fill only 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.
Cover with plastic lids and freeze, if desired.
Serves 40.
Approximately 156 calories per serving.

title: mincemeat
directions: Bring this
all
to a boil, stirring often to keep from scorching.	Fill jars and seal (cold packing 3 hours).

title: funnel cakes
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs with milk.
Add dry ingredients. Using a funnel with 3/8-inch spout, hold finger over the spout and pour some of the batter into funnel.
Hold funnel over hot oil in frying pan or fryer.
Release batter in circular or crisscross pattern.
Batter should dry rapidly.
If too thick, add 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons milk.
Fry about 1 minute; turn and fry 1/2 minute.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or sugar and cinnamon.

title: brend's best baked chicken
directions: Place
chicken	breasts between sheets of wax paper and pound lightly, just to flatten slightly.	Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and
mustard.
Dip chicken breasts, one at a time, into mixture, then
into bread crumbs.
Arrange chicken in lightly oiled shallow
baking
dish.
Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes or until cooked through.
Serve immediately.

title: mom's (apple) cobbler or other fruits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.
In a saucepan heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples.

title: peach tarts
directions: Put 1/4 pound of butter and cream cheese and cream together with flour.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll on a floured board.
Cut into squares.
Fill with peach preserves.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: fried eggs
directions: Break the eggs into a bowl.
Mix and put in a little bit of salt. Make the pan really hot.
Wait 10 seconds.
Then put 2 spoons of oil in the pan.
Wait 10 seconds again.
Put eggs in the pan, then flip until you can see it's cooked. Then you're done!

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread slices with margarine.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish and set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Spoon over bread slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, half and half and salt; mix well and pour over cheese.

title: no bake strawberry pie
directions: Make jello according to directions on box.
Put whole strawberries on bottom of graham cracker crust until full.
Add liquid jello and chill.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in sugar and mayonnaise.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in cupcake liners in muffin tin.
Freeze solid.
May top with dollop of whipped cream and a cherry.
May also freeze in a cake pan. Makes 20 to 24 cupcake size servings.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° until hot.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken; chop and set aside.
Cook rice according to directions on box.
Cook broccoli.
Saute onion, celery and pepper in margarine.
Add all ingredients together, stirring until cheese melts.
(If mixture seems dry, you may add a small amount of chicken broth until it seems moist enough.)
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: weight watchers snickers bars
directions: Mix ice cream, Cool Whip and peanut butter together.
Stir in dry chocolate pudding mix.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving has 1 milk, 1 protein, 1 fruit, 1 fat and 32 optional calories.

title: ranch stew
directions: In kettle, brown hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then cook on low for several hours.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and core apples; slice in thin slices and put in a lightly greased round pie pan.
Mix oats, brown sugar and flour; add margarine and stir until crumbly.
Put mixture on apples. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: 8 layer salad
directions: Use large container.
Add each layer in order listed.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight.
Toss right before serving.

title: crescent roll surprises
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll and separate dough.
Spread a little melted butter on one side of dough.
Put candy bar at small end of dough and roll up.
Pinch ends together.
Dip slightly in melted butter.
Bake about 15 minutes (until golden).
Sprinkle top with sugar or make a glaze to drizzle on top.

title: fix-n-mix bran muffins
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Add buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Mix until moist; seal in refrigerator up to 6 weeks. Grease muffin pans and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pudding ice cream
directions: Pour cold cream into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into 2-quart covered plastic container.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.

title: laverne's bean casserole
directions: Mix; pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed cheese crackers and 1/2 stick oleo.
Bake at 350° at least 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot barbecue pork
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients (onion, celery, garlic and butter) until tender.
Put in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients into crock-pot.
Stir occasionally.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low setting. Before serving, add water if too thick, or add flour if too watery.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; add milk, vanilla and egg yolks.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture begins to thicken, add margarine.
Filling is done when thick and forms a peak.
Add coconut and put in pie shell.
Use egg whites to make meringue. Brown meringue in oven.

title: just for kids: larhett's peanut butter pies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and Karo to soft ball stage.
Add peanuts and cook to 300° or hard crackle stage, plus one minute.
Remove from heat; add margarine, soda and salt.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Will foam up, so use 3-quart pan.
Pour on two cookie sheets covered with foil and buttered.
Spread out thin and let cool.
Break into pieces and store in tight container.
Makes lots!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry the bacon and crumble. Add grease from bacon to the salad dressing, sugar, vinegar and cheese.
Pour mixture over cut up raw broccoli.

title: aunt mary's strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O per directions.
Add strawberries, bananas, nuts, and pineapple.
Pour half of this in dish and then add sour cream. Place the remainder of the mixture over the sour cream and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: ham mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in water; set aside.
Dissolve mustard in small amount of broth.
Combine remaining broth with eggs.
Cook in saucepan about 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Beat in mayonnaise, onion and horseradish.
Chill until partially set.
Add sour cream and fold in ham.
Season with pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: frozen cheese cake
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham cracker crust.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift flour and make hole as for making biscuits.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and shortening.
Work together in flour until sugar does not feel grainy on hands.
Work dough well.
Roll out small pieces and pat thin in hand, or roll thin with rolling pin and cut with cutter.
Put on greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° to 350° for 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: easy barbecued hot dogs
directions: Put about 3 packages hot dogs in bottom of roasting pan.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over hot dogs.
Cook at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve on warm hot dog buns.
Plan on 3 to 4 hot dogs per man.

title: peanut pinwheel candy
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla with hand.
If it's too dry, add a few drops of milk.
Divide into three parts.
Roll out on wax paper, using your hand to flatten mixture out.
Spread peanut butter on top of mixture evenly.
Roll up and cut size you want. Store in refrigerator.

title: brown rice
directions: Bring water to a steady boil.
Add Lipton onion soup mix. Stir until it's dissolved.
Add rice to boiling water and stir well.
Add La Choy sauce to desired taste.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine
all ingredients and stir well.
Carefully drop batter by
tablespoons
into
a
deep
hot vat of salad oil or shortening.
Cook only a few at a time turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salt water until tender; drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.

title: fluffy potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; beat 2 to 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Spread crushed onions evenly over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine rice, onion, bell pepper, chicken, water chestnuts, soup, pimientos, green beans, mayonnaise and 1 cup of grated cheese.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with remaining cheese, cracker crumbs and almonds.
Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry refrigerator dessert
directions: Line an 8-inch pan with crushed vanilla wafers.
Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg, vanilla extract and nuts.
Spoon cream mixture over crumbs.
Top with strawberries, spreading evenly. Spread whipped cream over strawberries, and line sides of pan with the whole vanilla wafers.
May be topped with more strawberries, if desired.
Refrigerate for 2 to 6 hours.

title: marshmallows
directions: Soak the gum arabic in one cupful of the water and the orange-flower water.
Heat and melt it in a double boiler, then strain through a fine sieve.
Dissolve the crushed sugar with the remaining water, add the cream of tartar and boil to 245°, or until it forms a firm ball when tried in cold water.
Beat up the whites of the eggs to a stiff froth; beat in the vanilla and granulated sugars.
Mix the hot syrup with the dissolved gum and the beaten whites of eggs and beat until white and sufficiently firm to run into starch impressions.
Dust over with cornstarch and set aside for twelve hours.

title: garlic salad
directions: Mix together salt, garlic powder, liquid garlic and mayonnaise and refrigerate overnite.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Wash oysters, reserving liquid.
Place oysters, 3 teaspoons butter, liquid and water in saucepan.
Add potato and onion; cut fine.
Cook over low heat until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup milk slowly before serving.
Yields 4 servings.
A good first course in any meal.

title: millionaires
directions: In top of double boiler, melt caramels with milk, then add pecans and vanilla.
Mix well, using a teaspoon.
Drop spoonfuls of caramel-pecan mixture on cookie sheets sprayed with Pam.

(If cookie sheet has been placed in the freezer beforehand, this keeps hot caramel mixture from spreading too much on the cookie sheet.) Can also put cookie sheet back in freezer with caramel-pecan mixture until ready to dip in chocolate.

title: grilled potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Scrub potatoes. Cut in half crosswise. Cut slits crosswise into potatoes 3/4-inch apart, leaving bottom edge intact. Set aside.

title: preston's chicken
directions: Roll chicken
in
melted
butter
and then in soup mix. Bake in Dutch
oven until done, about 400°.
You may need more soup mix, depending on size of chicken.

title: low sugar spice cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all water is absorbed.
Add applesauce, eggs, liquid sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in soda, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add vanilla after flour mixture.
Pour dough into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
(Equals 1 bread, 1/2 fruit and 1 1/2 fat for diabetics.)

title: easy kraut casserole
directions: In a flat baking dish, spread drained kraut on bottom.
Layer dry egg noodles over kraut.
Next layer mushrooms over noodles. Pour mushroom soup to cover all layers.
Place Polish sausage slices on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hit of the party appetizers
directions: Spread on party rye and put under broiler until bubbly.
May be stored in refrigerator two to three weeks.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Cream powdered sugar and cheese, then add Cool Whip.
Mix. Spread mixture on top of pie crust and top with 1 large can cherry pie filling.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt into mix.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cowboy casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain.
Brown onion in butter; add ground beef and brown.
Add seasonings and soups.
Mix in spaghetti.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour broth over chicken and add Veg-All.
Spread soup over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Mix melted butter, flour and milk together.
Pour over soup and spread.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: bar b qued shrimp
directions: Place the whole shrimp in a cast iron skillet, in a single layer.
Drizzle olive oil over the top of the shrimp, cover with cracked black pepper until black.
Add lots of salt, I am not a salt fan, so I just put 2 tablespoons of Kosher salt.
Squeeze the juice from two lemons over the shrimp.
Cover with Tabasco and Lea Perrins - more is better.
Using at least one stick of salted butter, cut up butter on top of the shrimp.
Cook over high heat and turn over as the shrimp turns pink.
Do Not Over Cook!
Serve with a salad and loaf of French bread.
The bread will be used to soak up the sauce.
Cover your table with newspaper, provide lots of paper towels to use as napkins.
This is better when prepared with fresh shrimp. If using frozen shrimp, allow shrimp to defrost.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat, bread, salt, pepper, onion and eggs.
Shape and brown in oil.
Mix gravy, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer for about 35 minutes.

title: ripe tomato chow chow
directions: Will also need 1 white sock.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans thoroughly.
In large bowl, combine all beans and toss lightly with onion and bell pepper.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add salts, pepper and oil; mix well.
Pour dressing over beans; mix to coat well.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: cranberry chicken thighs
directions: Mix together French dressing, onion soup and cranberry sauce; pour over chicken thighs.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 1 1/2 hours in covered baking dish.

title: peanut butter swirl brownies
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in 1-quart glass bowl.
Microwave (High) uncovered 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted, stirring once. Blend in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Grease bottom only of 8-inch square microwave safe baking dish.
Spread batter in dish; set aside.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; mix thoroughly with milk.
Fold in lime juice. Add food coloring, if desired.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar gradually until stiff.
Spread over pie and put under broiler until lightly browned.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: brenda's pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: nellie's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add 2 tablespoons butter while hot. Layer 1/2 of broccoli in large casserole dish.
Then mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Layer 1/2 of this over broccoli. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over this.
Repeat, making two layers of broccoli, soup mixture and cheese.
Spread crushed buttered saltines on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: golden glow punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pineapple-orange juice concentrate.
Add apple juice and 3 cups cold water.
Carefully pour in chilled ginger ale.
Serves 25 (4 ounce serving size).

title: play dough
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Cook until dough pulls away from sides of pan and forms a ball.
Take out of pan and knead dough.
Soak pan. Store in plastic bag and store in airtight container.

title: stay-a-bed stew
directions: Place beef, potatoes, carrots, onions and corn in a roasting pan.
Mix soups and liquid from peas and corn together.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Pour peas over the top of mixture.
Add wine to cover the top of the vegetables.
If needed, add some water to cover the top of the vegetables.

title: cheesy mushroom potatoes
directions: Mix together corn flakes and melted oleo.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan sprayed with Pam.
Cover with corn flake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 people.

title: diet grapefruit with triple sec dessert
directions: Carefully peel and segment grapefruit.
Place segments in pretty serving bowl.
Add 4 to 5 halved cherries.
Just before serving, stir in 1 to 2 tablespoons Triple Sec or Cointreau. Serves 1.

title: raspberry ribbon pie
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add raspberries and lemon juice; stir until berries thaw.
Chill until partially set.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Beat well. Fold in whipped cream.
Alternate jello mixture and cream cheese mixture in crust, making 4 layers.
Refrigerate until firm. Garnish with raspberries.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat with mixture. Brown meat slowly on both sides in hot oil.
Combine next 5 ingredients and pour over meat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Add onions.
Put into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until fork-tender.
Serves 6.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Layer rice, then chicken and broccoli.
Pour mixture of chicken soup and mayonnaise over all in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle one 12 ounce package grated Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, covered.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Boil all ingredients, except peanut butter, oatmeal and coconut, for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, oatmeal and coconut.
Drop on waxed paper. Chill.

title: crescent ragoo
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add spices and tomato paste and cook until warm.
Mix together cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese and set aside.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in pie shell at 350° until mixture is thick and makes a crust over the top.

title: jim's mustard-onion bread
directions: Pat or roll out dough until about 1-inch thick.
Spread on mustard;
sprinkle	onion
flakes
over
mustard.
Roll
up dough (like for rolls); pinch ends of dough.
Place in greased bread pan; cover	and let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45
minutes (or until golden).
This makes great sandwiches.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in olive oil, then add other ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.
Separately combine 1 cup creamy cottage cheese, 2 cups Ricotta cheese, 2 tablespoons chopped parsley, 1 beaten egg, 1 tablespoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Cook a 10 ounce box lasagna noodles.
In a baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese mixture and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: western winter salad
directions: Core, rinse and drain lettuce; chill.
Combine sour cream, oil, vinegar, onion, sugar, salt and thyme.
Chill if you wish. Cut olives into halves; tear lettuce into bite size pieces (5 cups).
Core and dice apple; toss with lettuce, olives and cream mixture in salad bowl.
Serve at once.

title: chess bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Over low heat, melt the butter and brown sugar.
Add all remaining ingredients except powdered sugar. Place in a greased and floured 13 x 9 pan and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: ham, cheese, egg omelette
directions: Mix bread, meat, cheese and mushrooms together and put into 10 x 14-inch oven-proof serving dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce and pour over all ingredients. Put in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Silver knife should come out almost dry.
Serves ten easily.
Great for company brunch.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Soak in water; squeeze out excess water with your hands.
Add bread and beef and season with salt, pepper and chopped onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Add sour cream and mix well.

title: old fashioned boiled coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks and milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add vinegar and oleo.
Mix well and cool.
Put in jar and refrigerate.

title: buffet rice
directions: Cook rice and beans using package directions. Saute garlic and onion in oil until soft.
Mix Ricotta with 3 cups of the Jack cheese.
Layer this mixture alternately in a greased, shallow 12-cup casserole with cheese and Ricotta spread evenly over casserole.
End with rice mixture. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. During the last 5 minutes, top with remaining Jack cheese and finish baking. Serves 6.

title: m & m cookies
directions: Cream sugars with shortening.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups M & M's.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt shortening.
Add cocoa.
Mix thoroughly and set aside. Beat eggs on high speed until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and mix at medium speed. Blend in vanilla, water, cocoa and shortening mixture.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread batter on lightly greased sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes and cut while warm.

title: cool mandarin dessert
directions: Drain oranges, reserving the juice. Add enough water to juice to measure 1 cup. Refrigerate the oranges. In a large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in reserved juice. Add sherbet, stirring until dissolved. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until thickened. Keep 10 orange segments refrigerated for garnish. Fold remaining oranges into gelatin mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, garnish with the reserved oranges.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Individual pie shells can also be used. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: corn and squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until done.
Drain well.
Add corn, sour cream, corn bread mix and margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Take out of oven and top with grated cheese.
Let cheese melt down into mixture.
Serve.

title: french onion dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add sour cream and beat on low with hand mixer until well mixed.
Then beat on high for 2 minutes.
Add onion soup mix and beat until well blended. Store in refrigerator.
When ready to use, let mix come to room temperature and serve with crackers, chips or vegetables (carrots, celery, green peppers, cucumbers).

title: southern fried hot water corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add boiling hot water and mix until smooth.
Should be thick.
Drop or form patties.
Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Great with ham hocks and greens.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to boil.
Reduce heat immediately and stir with wooden spoon until well blended.
Brush over meat or game to be cooked.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and continue to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour.
Add extract.
Add 7-Up.
Heat oven to 350°. Allow to cook for approximately 45 minutes to an hour.
I usually use butter and margarine wrappers to grease cake pan.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Combine cake mix and baking soda, then proceed according to package directions on cake mix box, substituting the pumpkin for the last addition of liquid.
Fold in nuts and dates.
Bake in 1 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pan.
Bake as directed on package.
You may use white or yellow cake mix with spices added as suggested on package, adding soda at same time.
Add 1 cup pumpkin instead of last addition of liquid.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring 6 cups water to a boil in a 3-quart Dutch oven.
Add broccoli and onion.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Add cheese and seasonings, stirring until cheese melts.
Stir in milk, half and half and butter.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Combine flour and cold water, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add to broccoli mixture, stirring constantly. Heat until thickened.
(If too thick, add a little water.)
May have to add a little more flour and water to make right consistency.
(Do not make too thick.)

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: In a saucepan combine all ingredients except chicken.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Pour half the sauce over the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Baste with remaining sauce every 15 minutes during cooking.
To reduce fat in this recipe, remove skin from chicken before cooking.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Add both sauces and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Boil noodles, then strain.
Pour noodles into 12 x 17-inch cake pan.
Add Cheddar cheese; stir in sauce mixture.
Top with Mozzarella, then pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peppy veggy
directions: In medium saucepan, combine beef bouillon and vegetable juice; bring to boil.
Stir in Tabasco.
Remove from heat.
Serve in mug with lime slices.
Contains 36 calories per serving.

title: pineapple raisin drops
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and dredge fruit with part.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add fruit and nuts.
Last add vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and cook about 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Freezes very well.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add pineapple, eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Do not use electric mixer.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in nuts.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: greek stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan, heat oil and saute onion for 10 minutes.
Combine all the remaining ingredients except tomatoes and add to the onion.
Stuff filling into tomatoes.
Bake for 15 minutes and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onions, covered, in butter about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add condensed beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; bring to boiling. Sprinkle toasted bread with cheese; place under broiler until cheese is lightly browned.

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot (not boiling) water.
Set aside. Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well and until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in melted chocolate and chopped walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven 10 minutes.
Remove immediately. Makes approximately 36 cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add corn syrup and eggs (one at a time). Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump cake mix in bowl.
Mix package of Jell-O in 2/3 cup water.
Add to cake mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes in tube pan at 350°.

title: chicken wings
directions: Separate chicken wing pieces. Combine all ingredients. Place chicken wings in mixture and marinate 3 hours. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Add cocoa and soda to water; let stand until rest of cake is mixed.
Cream butter and sugar gradually.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Add sifted flour alternately with milk.
Add cocoa mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Pour into well greased loaf or layer cake pans and bake in 350° oven. Frost with fudge frosting.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to 1 package Jell-O in a small stainless steel bowl; stir to dissolve.
Pour half of Jell-O in a 9 x 13-inch pan and place on level shelf in fridge to chill.
Set the small metal bowl with remaining dissolved Jell-O in a large bowl of ice.

title: pan-fried eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant halves crosswise into 1/2 inch slices.
Combine cracker crumbs, parsley, salt, and pepper.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture.
Coat with crumb mixture on both sides.
Heat oil in large frying pan.
When hot, add eggplant slices, a few at a time.
Cook about 2 to 3 minutes per side, turning once, until golden.
Drain on paper towels or absorbent brown paper.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in large iron skillet.
Sprinkle sugar over butter and arrange pineapple slices on sugar.
(Place whole maraschino cherry in center of each pineapple slice, if desired, also can place pecan halves decoratively around pineapple slices, if desired.)
Pour cake batter evenly over pineapple and bake at 350° until done.
Let stand in skillet for 5 minutes.
Then turn out on cake plate with pineapple side up.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water, adding juice and marshmallows, then bring to boil.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil.
Add cranberries; cook until berries "pop."
Remove from heat.
Add dry jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Put in dish. Refrigerate.

title: party rye pizzas
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly and spread on party rye rounds. Broil until cheese melts, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: appetizer log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, ham and mustard; mix until well blended. Stir in Cheddar cheese and chives. Chill.
Shape into log. Roll in peanuts. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix Kool aid as directed on package.
Then add all of juices. Mix well and chill.
When ready to serve slice one orange in half, and slice each half very thin.
Top punch in punch bowl with orange slices.

title: crunchy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl, gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt in a small mixing bowl; stir into creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoon, 3 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheets, and cool on wire racks.
Yields 10 dozen.
Note:
One cup flaked coconut may be added to batter.

title: grandma eloise's gingerbread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Add remaining ingredients and mix, then add 1 cup boiling water with a good teaspoon soda. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Delicious!!

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in large roaster.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium heat; cook for 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour over popcorn, stirring and turning.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on waxed paper to cool. Break up and store in an airtight container.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, melted butter, buttermilk and vanilla; mix well and stir in coconut flakes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 300° and bake until golden brown.

title: spicy chicken and corn
directions: Cook chicken in butter until done.
Remove from pan.
Add onion and bell pepper with seasonings in pan; cook until tender. Stir in soup, tomatoes and rice.
Heat to boiling.
Add cooked chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir often.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together oleo, flour and nuts and pat onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix together 8 ounces of cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip and pour over first layer.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Pour this over second layer.
Let set and chill.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: poppy cock (chicken)
directions: Combine condensed soup and poppy seed.
Mix well.
Dip each piece of chicken in soup mixture.
Then coat well with Cheddar cheese cracker crumbs.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until fork-tender.
Serves 4.

title: ms. supan's egg rolls
directions: Heat oil.
Brown meat until done.
Add vegetables and beaten egg.
Stir 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce.
Remove from heat.
Drop by spoonfuls of filling to each egg roll skin.
Wrap and seal with egg white.
Deep-fry until golden brown.

title: country molasses cookies
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, molasses and vinegar in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Cool.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Add eggs to cooled molasses mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Put 2 tablespoons bacon grease in casserole dish with the chipped fried bacon and all ingredients.
Mix good. Freeze.
Thaw and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: honey glazed potatoes
directions: In saucepan, cover potatoes with salted water.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
In skillet, melt butter.
Stir in water, honey, salt and pepper.
Stirring occasionally, cook 1 layer of potatoes 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Add chocolate pudding mix and 1/4 cup water and mix well.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: hermits
directions: Mix in usual manner and bake.

title: spicy beef dip for tortilla chips
directions: Microwave in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Saute beef, onion and garlic 4 to 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain; stir in tomato sauce, ketchup, oregano and sugar.
Cover and cook 5 to 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Add cream cheese and Parmesan and stir until cream cheese melts.
Serve warm with nacho chips.
Makes 3 cups dip.

title: dump cake
directions: Preset oven on high 325°.
In glass casserole oblong dish, layer all ingredients in this order:
First layer, pineapple layered in pan; second layer, apple filing; third layer, Duncan Hines cake mix; fourth layer, pecans.
Bake on high 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: raisin rice
directions: Cook rice. Saute onions and almonds in butter until a gentle brown. Add raisins; heat thoroughly. When rice is done cooking, mix everything together. Add salt to taste.

title: pea pickin' good cake
directions: Beat together.
Bake in 2 round pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pink elephant salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and pineapple juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: ham and potato bake
directions: Dice and boil potatoes.
Add flour, milk, ham, potatoes and cheese in a casserole dish.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°, then melt cheese on top for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pudding
directions: Combine blueberries, 3/4 c. sugar and lemon juice in a small saucepan over moderate heat until sugar dissolves and mixture simmers. Remove from heat and set aside to cool to lukewarm. Cream butter, remaining 1/2 c. sugar and vanilla on medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add egg; beat until well blended. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Fold in lukewarm blueberry mixture. Pour into a greased and floured 9 inch pie plate and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Serve warm with lemon sauce, if desired.

title: delightful dip(blender)
directions: Divide cheese into small cubes.
Put in blender and blend. Add liquid ingredients.
Last, add onion and dried beef (tuna or crabmeat may be used in place of beef).
Beat until well blended; refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg, then dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix will be flakey.
Roll into balls.
Roll in sugar; flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon crunch coffee cake
directions: Sprinkle yeast over water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add eggs, white sugar, salt and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Blend thoroughly.
Beat about 50 strokes. Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let rise at 85° to 90° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes until light and doubled in size.
Combine next 4 ingredients and remaining flour. Sprinkle over dough. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown. Blend remaining ingredients together. Spread over top of coffee cake.

title: chicken marengo
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in shortening; pour off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir now and then.
Uncover; cook until desired consistency.
Serve with fine buttered noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger meat casserole
directions: Brown together ground beef, salt and sugar.
Add tomato sauce. Simmer 20 minutes.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream, cream cheese and chopped (very fine) onion.
Cook noodles.
In casserole, spread in layers the noodles, meat, cheese mixture.
Repeat and cover with sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(This recipe may be frozen and reheated.)

title: cheesy cheese ball
directions: Mix together. Roll in crushed pecans.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Mix all wet ingredients Mix all together. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour 10 minutes in a tube or bundt pan. Can be made in 3 layer cake pans, just reduce cooking time. Put 1 pkg. walnuts or pecans in cake mix and save some to put on the cake.

title: daiquiri dream
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and whirl until ice cubes are crushed.
Yield:
3 servings (1 1/2 cups).
Serving size:
1/2 cup.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze dry spinach.
Stir in 1 package soup mix, sour cream and salad dressing until well blended.
Add water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Stir before serving.
Makes about 4 cups.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake 325 degree for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone. Cover bottom of casserole with bite size pieces.
Cover with soup.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all but cheese.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased preheated skillet.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Pour remaining batter on top of cheese.
Cook at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 1 large black skillet full.

title: olive crackers
directions: Place Ritz crackers on a serving dish.
Top each cracker with cheese spread.
Place one olive on top of cracker cheese spread. Serve.
Delicious with any type of beverage.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix ingredients and form in small balls.
Mix the following sauce ingredients in shallow glass baking dish.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Wash and separate cauliflower; drain.
Heat shortening in a large skillet covering bottom.
Beat eggs in milk, dipping cauliflower in mixture, then dip in flour.
Fry to golden brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer each ingredient in large bowl.
Seal with mayonnaise. Store in refrigerator overnight and toss before serving.
Salad will keep 2 days after tossing.
Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: mama's fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits
and
nuts.	Pour
Eagle Brand milk over the fruit mixture and stir gently.

title: siberian chicken
directions: Rub chicken with Hawaiian salt, pepper and garlic.
Set aside. In a food processor or blender, chop bread into crumbs on slice (4 pieces at a time).
Empty crumbs into large mixing bowl.
Add chopped parsley and shredded cheese.
Mix together by hand.
Dip chicken, 1 piece at a time, first in melted butter, then roll in crumb mixture until evenly coated.
Place pieces in 9 x 12-inch roasting pan, lined with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes, or until crumb coating is golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger barley vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in large dutch oven or soup pot.
Drain.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add powdered sugar and corn starch. Beat until light and fluffy.
Add flour.
Press into lightly greased and floured 15 X 10 X 1 inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and celery in margarine until softened.
Mix bread cubes and crumbled cornbread in a large bowl.
Add beaten egg and chicken broth.
Stir in onion, celery and margarine.
Add sage, seasoning, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Spread dressing in pan.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy dessert pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar, vanilla, 2 egg yolks and 1 egg.
Pour into an ovenproof dish and bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Beat the egg whites until soft peaks form, then gradually add 4 tablespoons sugar and beat until stiff.
After removing the pudding from the oven, spread meringue on top of it and return the dish to the oven for about 10 minutes or until nicely brown on top.
Cool in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage and hamburg soup
directions: You can use more cabbage, mushrooms or beans.
May have to add more water.

title: mix for kids
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine cereals, peanuts and pretzels together and set aside.
Melt butter in a shallow pan (13 x 9-inch) in the oven.
Add the Worcestershire sauce.
Slowly stir in the cereal mixture until evenly coated.
Bake for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix can of soup and water; stir until blended. Add chicken, celery and onion. Add 1 cup chow mein noodles. Sprinkle remaining chow mein noodles on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: baked apples
directions: Place apple in baking dish; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add sweetener; cover tightly.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 60 minutes, until done.
Yield: 1 serving.
Carbohydrate 20 g, protein .03 g, fat .5 g, calories 78.
One serving = 1 1/2 fruit exchanges.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on box.
Drain noodles thoroughly and add butter while hot.
In large bowl, beat eggs and add noodles, vanilla, sugar, pineapple and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with fresh, cut fruit.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef, drain fat and cool.
Shred lettuce, dice tomatoes and crush Dorito chips.
Drain olives.
Combine all ingredients, including cheese.
Just before serving, mix in salad dressing.

title: oatmeal caramel bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; stir in oil and egg. Put half of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Spread ice cream topping on top. Crumble remaining dough over. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sister's sweet sour pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in 1/3 cup salt to each quart of water.
Drain and dry.
Boil vinegar, water and sugar until clear. Add cucumbers and simmer until they lose their grass green color. Place spices and dill in bottom of jar; add pickles.
Cover with hot syrup.
Place dill on top and seal.

title: beef roll mozzarella
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, onion, egg and bread crumbs. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add mushroom liquid to meat mixture.
Mix lightly.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs at high speed until well beaten.
Add sugar and beat until dissolved.
Add flavoring and evaporated milk and mix well. Pour into freezer and add milk to the top.
Mix well and freeze. Makes 6 quarts.

title: butter frosting
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in a processor or with an electric mixer.
Add the cream gradually, stirring until frosting has good spreading consistency.
Stir in your choice of flavoring.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, spray with Pam.
Combine sugar, milk and flour.
Stir until mixed.
In the center of the dish, pour in pie filling.
Do not stir.
Slice margarine and place on top. Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: texas oven barbecue
directions: In small saucepan, combine coffee, catsup, onion, brown sugar, Worcestershire, lemon juice and spices.
Simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Place brisket in glass baking dish and pour about 1/2 the sauce over meat.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cooked brisket may be served warm or cold with remaining sauce.

title: creamy chicken and mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Add chicken, mushroom soup, milk and noodles.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes.
Add more milk if the soup becomes too thick.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream 2 1/4 cups sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add half of the flour, salt, baking powder, orange juice and vanilla. Add remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Peel and slice thinly 4 large apples.
Mix cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar.
Dip sliced apples in cinnamon mixture.
Put a layer of batter, layer of apples, etc., in a large ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn upside down on rack until cool or leave in pan to be cut from there.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Layer crust with chicken, then vegetables, then soup.
Adjust second crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Make pastry.
Roll out 1/2 and line a spring-form pan or a deep dish (10-inch) pie pan.
Roll out top crust and set aside.
Thaw and drain well the spinach.
Place in mixing bowl.
If cottage cheese is creamed, drain in a sieve.
Add to spinach along with parsley, onions, garlic, salt, pepper, ham and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put half of pepper rings in bottom of crust. Beat eggs well.
Pour over spinach mix.
Stir well.
Pour in pan over the red pepper rings.
Smooth out.
Lay rest of pepper rings on top, then scatter rest of Mozzarella over all.
Cover with top crust.
Seal edges and flute.
Make vents in top.
Brush with cream.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes more or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove sides of spring-form.
Cut in wedges to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cognac carrots(serves 12)
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add carrots and cognac.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a saucepan, put water, Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Heat until ingredients are mixed well.
In casserole dish, mix broccoli, onions, celery and rice together.
Add saucepan mixture to broccoli mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done.

title: company cauliflower *
directions: Separate cauliflower in medium pieces.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Brown mushrooms and green pepper lightly in oleo; blend in flour. Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly until thick; add salt.
Place 1/2 each of cauliflower, cheese and sauce in a 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake until lightly brown at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bacon cheesy potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray, layer sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt margarine and pour over potatoes; then sprinkle with chopped onions.
Heat milk and cheese together to make sauce.
Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika; then crumble bacon over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Uncover and continue baking, until brown on top.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Fold together until well blended.

title: easy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and salt in a pie plate.
Mix milk and egg together.
Dip chicken pieces in milk
mixture and then in flour mixture.
Place in a baking dish and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop fine.
Remove casing from sausage and cook with chopped stems, garlic and 1 tablespoons oil.
Cook until browned.
Add 1 tablespoon oil, parsley and cheese.
Fill mushroom caps.
Put in baking pan with remaining oil and 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: chili beef soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomato sauce, salt and cheese, in electric slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Stir in tomato sauce and salt.
Cover and cook on high setting for 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish servings with shredded cheese.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in box for 7 minutes on High.
Mix broccoli and all other ingredients in casserole; top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Cook on High 10 minutes.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Combine crabmeat, pepper, onion, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Put beaten egg in a 1-cup measuring cup and fill with milk.
Add egg mixture to crab mixture and toss lightly.
Put in foil crab shells.
Sprinkle with paprika and put a pat of butter on each.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Heat over medium heat the cocoa, sugar, milk and salt until a little of mixture dropped into cold water forms a ball.
Take off heat.
Add buttered and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into buttered dish; cool and cut in squares.

title: broccoli casserole *(official fbc staff christmas party recipe)
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Combine egg, soup, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Add broccoli.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt margarine and combine with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water and add 2 tablespoons sugar.
In another vessel, beat 3 eggs well.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup warm water, salt and enough flour to make a rather stiff batter.
Mix well and knead for 5 minutes.
Set to rise in a butter crock.
When double in bulk, turn in board and divide into 3 equal parts.
Roll each piece into a round 1/4-inch thick, spread with melted butter, then cut into 16 wedge-shaped pieces and roll, beginning at wide end.
Place on greased baking sheets, let double in size and bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: okra rice dressing
directions: Cook sausage in skillet.
Add onions, garlic, bell pepper and celery.
Fry until tender.
Add okra and rice.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: squash soup
directions: Cut skin off squash and sweet potatoes.
Boil water in a soup pot.
Add bouillon cube, herbs, parsley, sweet potatoes and squash.
Boil in medium heat.
When contents are almost soft, add 1 slice whole wheat bread and peeled apple.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes. Let cool.
Puree and serve.

title: congealed salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Mix in jello.
Let cool slightly.
Mix cheese, mayonnaise, pineapple and nuts together.
Mix everything together and put in refrigerator to mold.

title: pita pocket pizza
directions: Take 1 pita pocket.
Cut the edges to make 2 round pieces. Top with cheese and favorite topping.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, sugar, soda and oleo until crumbly. Then press half of the mixture in a 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over baked crumbs.
Melt caramels with evaporated milk and pour over top of other ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining crumbly mixture over top and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ham rolls
directions: Layer ham and cheese on tortillas.
Spread layer of spinach dip last.
Roll up tightly.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate until well chilled.
To use, cut into 1/8-inch slices for appetizers or cut in half or serve whole for a quick lunch.

title: chocolate drinksocorro, new mexico
directions: To serve:
Put 1/3 c. chocolate mix in cup, add hot water to fill.
If desired, marshmallow on top or scoop of ice cream.

title: sauerkraut and sausage
directions: In a heavy skillet, cook sausage and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in apples, sauerkraut, water and sugar.
Stir in ingredients well.
Allow to simmer, tightly covered, on a low fire, for about 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley just before serving.

title: fruit slush
directions: In a plastic or ice cube tray, freeze milk until almost solid. Turn into blender container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend until smooth and frothy.
Serves 2.

title: gabby hayes' cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Pat with wet fork.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Saute mushrooms and butter until soft.
Then add flour, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Place in buttered dish and spread cheese on top.
Bake in oven until cheese melts at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: english pea and cheese salad
directions: Drain peas and mushrooms.
In bowl, add all ingredients. Mix well.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate. Serve chilled.

title: cheese spread
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Whip slowly on mixer until fluffy.
Spread on sourdough French bread and toast under broiler.
Can be made up ahead of time.
Spread on bread and frozen.
Freezes very nicely.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until vegetables are soft.

title: coconut pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
On bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate, evenly spread the margarine.
Put coconut evenly into margarine.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden; cool.

title: orange flan
directions: Mix biscuits with butter.
Line a pie plate.

title: moni's potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise, then cut into even wedges.
Boil potato wedges for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Pat dry.
Spread potato wedges in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with oil, spices and herbs.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in 1 large container of Cool Whip.
Store in freezer until ready to serve.

title: grapefruit souffle salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add grapefruit juice, vinegar and mayonnaise.
With rotary or electric beater, mix until well blended.
Pour into 4-cup refrigerator tray.
Chill until partially set.
Turn mixture into bowl and beat until fluffy. Fold in grapefruit and celery. Return to tray. Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
If desired, top each serving with a grapefruit section.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Melt first three ingredients in a boiler.
Pour over the hash browns.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until brown on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and chill.
Roll into 2 or 3 rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil and freeze until ready to use.

title: herb rice
directions: Brown rice in margarine in heavy skillet, stirring frequently. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken in a bowl and put flour and salt all over it. Then heat oil in skillet; add chicken and remaining ingredients and let simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Stir in onion. Mix well. Add egg and milk. Mix well and let sit about 1/2 hour to rise. Do not stir again even when dipping out to cook. Dip small portions (ice teaspoon-size) into deep, hot Wesson oil at about 375°. Cook until brown and done in middle. Good with seafood.

title: green wreaths
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows. Add vanilla, food coloring and cornflakes. Form wreaths. Decorate with cinnamon candies and red sugar.

title: good-quick punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water, sugar and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale, chilled, just before serving in punch bowl.

title: baked rice fluff
directions: Blend egg yolks, onion, butter and cheese.
Add parsley.
Pour over cooked rice and mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into rice mixture.
Pour into 2-quart greased casserole and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix onion soup, water and rice in casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour cream of chicken soup over all.
Bake at 350°, covered, until done.

title: greasepaint
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a dish.
This is the white greasepaint.
Set aside half of the white greasepaint.
Divide the rest into 3 equal parts.
Put each part in a separate dish.
Mix a different shade of food coloring into each part.
Lightly spread cold cream or shortening on your face.
Use a tissue to wipe off any extra.
Use fingers to spread on white greasepaint over entire face.
Spread in one direction.
Keep away from eyes.
Use paintbrush to apply colored paint.
To take off, use baby oil on a tissue.

title: strawberry danish
directions: Cook danish dessert and let cool.
Wash, cap and slice berries. Cream the cheese and sugar; add Cool Whip and mix.
Line pan with vanilla wafers.
Cover with cheese mixture, then add strawberries to danish mix and pour over cheese mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs well.
Mix in dry ingredients, then add milk slowly.
Bake in 9 x 13 greased pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and vanilla with butter to soft ball stage (235°).
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Beat until stiff; pour into buttered pan.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas in hot oil in skillet.
Mix cheese, onion and chicken in bowl.
Spoon onto tortillas; roll to enclose filling. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend chicken broth, flour and salt in saucepan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add jalapeno peppers.
Blend in sour cream.
Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Yields 1 dozen.

title: j.d.'s tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
In a large casserole dish, mix both cans of soup, 2/3 package of cheese and tuna.
Once noodles are tender, drain and mix well into tuna mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top has melted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and rice in butter over low heat until vegetables are transparent and rice is golden.
Add salt, pepper, thyme and chicken broth.
(You can make this skillet version of pilaf with canned chicken broth or with chicken bouillon.)
Cover skillet with a tight-fitting lid and cook over low heat until broth is absorbed, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: honey yogurt dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients until blended.
Refrigerate until used.

title: creamy chicken salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni or shells according to package directions; drain well.
Cool.
(Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well.)

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in the oil until smooth.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir
dry
ingredients
into egg mixture.
Add nuts and apple
and mix
well.
Turn
into
a greased and floured 11 x 7-inch pan and
bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool cake in pan or on a rack and spread smoothly with icing.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar and Crisco together.
Add the eggs, almond, flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda; mix well. Add chopped nuts.
Shape into long rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill dough for 1 hour.
Slice thin.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: green beans gretel
directions: Pour liquid from beans, saving 1/4 cup of liquid.
Fry the chopped onion in margarine until limp and tender.
Combine the 1/4 cup saved liquid with sugar, vinegar and cornstarch.
Add mixture to onions.
Stir until thickened and smooth.
Blend in prepared mustard and horseradish.
Add beans.
Heat gently until hot.

title: cheese dip or ball
directions: Mix together.
If making a ball, roll in another 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: cold bread pudding
directions: Slice open biscuits and put into deep pie pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over sliced bread.
Cook at 350° in preheated oven for 15 minutes.

title: grand marnier whipped cream truffles
directions: Arrange forty 1 1/2-inch foil candy cups or small paper cups on a baking sheet.
Using a fine sieve or sifter, sift a heavy layer of confectioners sugar into cups.
Have ready a pastry bag fitted with a star tip.

title: coconut pecan icing
directions: Cook and stir often over medium heat until thickened (about 12 minutes).
Remove from heat, add coconut and nuts.
Cool until thick enough to spread.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli according to package and drain well.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in a Pyrex bowl that may be placed in an oven.
Heat for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with chips or veggie dippers.
Keep warm in chafing dish.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Mash the berries.
Add berries, sugar and egg white to mixer bowl and beat until stiff.
Serve with milk and strawberries.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and cool.
Chop onion, celery, hard-cooked eggs and add to macaroni.
Drain shrimp and wash and add.
Mix with mayonnaise and Salad Supreme seasoning to taste.

title: lentil soup
directions: Wash lentils, drain, add to 3 quarts water in a soup pot.
Add salt, large clove garlic and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer, adding more water, if needed, for about 1 hour.
While lentils are cooking, in a saucepan, place olive oil and garlic clove.
Cook over medium heat until garlic is lightly browned.
Do not scorch.
Add tomatoes, salt and basil.
Simmer slowly to make a sauce.
In a separate pot, boil pasta and drain.
To finish soup, add sauce and pasta to lentils and serve hot.

title: easy chicken with mushrooms
directions: Coat rinsed chicken pieces with flour, salt and pepper.
Cook in hot oil or shortening approximately 15 minutes, or until brown. Drain off fat.
Add mushrooms, white wine, onion, garlic and tarragon, parsley and peppers, if desired.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice, noodles or cooked potatoes.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease pans.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy. Beat 5 minutes longer. Sift together flour, cocoa, powder, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with water and vanilla.
Bake layers about 35 minutes, oblong pan 40 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Line bottom with bread. Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Add sausage on top of cheese.
Beat eggs, 1 cup of milk, mustard, onion, salt and pepper and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
This is a must!!
Remove from refrigerator.
Mix soup with remaining 1/4 cup milk and spread on top of casserole.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 300°, then uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: beans
directions: Put beans in a pot and cover with water and bring to a full boil and then put on simmer.
Add garlic and salt.
Cover and cook about 4 hours.
Make sure water level of beans stays just above beans.
In another pan, brown 1 pound of diced bacon; drain fat, leaving about 3 tablespoons drippings in the pan.
Add ham, onions, tomatoes and chiles; saute.
When beans are soft, add sauteed ingredients and bacon to bean pot and simmer about 20 minutes. Ready to serve.
Tastes good poured over rice and makes a meal.

title: party potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Drain.
Mash while hot.
Add sour cream, cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until well blended. Place in casserole.
May be made a day or two ahead and reheated.

title: ranch style casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Pour into large casserole dish. Add tomatoes, beans and top with cheese.
Mix cornbread and pour on top.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook until done; test with toothpick.
Makes 6 servings.

title: veg-all cheesy chowder
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Add flour, whisk and cook 1 minute on low heat, stirring often.
Add milk and broth.
Cook on medium heat, stirring until thickened. Add cheese and seasoning, stirring until cheese is melted.
Add Veg-All and parsley.
Reduce heat and cook until heated thoroughly, but do not boil.

title: festive punch
directions: Add all ingredients at one time to a gallon jar.
Add water to make 1 gallon.

title: mom's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a 10-inch cast-iron skillet, melt butter.
Sprinkle brown sugar over melted butter, then place pineapple rings evenly over top.

title: mom's cream of chicken and potato soup
directions: Combine the 2 cans of soup in a medium-size pot.
Add the can of evaporated milk, the butter, the package of chicken flavoring, the pepper and onion powder.
Stir with a spoon until well blended.

title: grilled steaks with garlic crumbs
directions: Pat steak dry with paper towels.
Mix the mustard, wine and pepper.
Spread mixture on both sides of steak using about 2/3 of the mixture.
Grill steak over hot coals or 5 to 6 inches from source of heat, turning once, for 25 minutes for medium-rare.

title: key lime pie
directions: In large, heat resistant, bowl, dissolve gelatin in hot water. Stir in yogurt with wire whisk. Fold in whipped topping. Spread in bottom of
crust. Refrigerate overnight or 2 hours.

title: grilled swordfish steaks
directions: In large dish, arrange swordfish in single layer.
In small bowl, combine oil, soy sauce, sherry, ginger root, orange peel and pepper.
Pour marinade over fish and marinate in refrigerator overnight, turning occasionally.
Cook over glowing coals, basting with marinade for 4 to 5 minutes per side or until firm to touch.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne 9 minutes.
Pour cold water over until you can handle lasagne.
Spread thin layer of meat sauce on bottom of casserole pan.
Layer lasagne, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella, lasagne, meat sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mock steak
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients and make into patties. Brown in small amount of shortening.
Place in long baking dish. Mix together soups; pour over patties.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except chow mein noodles.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Place chow mein noodles on just before you eat.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Add Jell-O mixture; stir. Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple. Add to other ingredients. Add marshmallows; fold. Cover and chill.

title: salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and Cool Whip until well blended.
Add cottage cheese and fruit cocktail, stirring until mixed well.
Put in bowl and chill.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix with spoon by hand flour, sugar and beer.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and let rise 5 minutes.
Pour the melted butter or margarine over dough and bake 50 minutes in 375° oven.

title: tirami su(coffee syrup)
directions: Combine syrup ingredients in a pan and boil 5 minutes.
Cool at room temperature.
Slice pound cake in 1/2-inch slices and line the bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pour enough syrup over to
soak all the slices.
Whip the cream until thick, then fold in 3 tablespoons of orange marmalade.
Cover soaked pound cake with a thin layer of whipped cream.
Cover this with another layer of previously dipped cake slices.
Cover with remaining cream and refrigerate.
Before serving, spread cocoa gently over the cream. This cake is to be dished out with a spoon.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and chop broccoli flowers; wash, peel and chop stems. Combine all ingredients.
Chill in covered container for at least 2 hours.
Eggs may be omitted for low-cholesterol dish.

title: broccoli-cauliflower cooked salad
directions: Cook broccoli, cauliflower and Oriental vegetables together until tender.
Drain and add soups.
Put in ovenware bowl and sprinkle cracker crumbs and melted butter on top.
Cook approximately 15 minutes at 450°.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Beat egg well.
Add milk and soda.
Then beat in rest of ingredients until smooth.
Pour onto hot griddle.
Makes about 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: spicy red beans and vegetable rice
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water to a depth of 2 inches above beans.
Let soak 8 hours.
Drain and rinse beans.
Set beans aside.
Coat pan with cooking spray; add oil.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.
Add beans, water and next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Remove and discard bay leaves.
Place 1/2 cup Vegetable Rice in each of 8 individual serving bowls; top each evenly with bean mixture.

title: upside down pecan apple pie
directions: Combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine in 9 inch pan. Spread evenly over bottom.
Lay one pie crust over pecan mixture. Combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large bowl, mixing lightly.
Spoon into pan.
Top with remaining crust, folding top crust edge under bottom crust.
Press together to seal and flute.
Cut slits in top crust.
Place baking sheet on lower oven rack to catch any drips.
Bake 40-50 minutes at 375 degrees on middle oven rack or until apples are tender and crust is golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Place large round platter over top of pie and invert onto plate.
Cool at least 1 hour before serving.

title: cheating chilli
directions: In large pot, put pintos and a little salt.
In the meantime, have ground beef frying.
Add tomato paste to beans, rinsing cans. Chop onion and add to bean and tomato mixture.
Then add cooked and drained beef.
Mix 1 pack of chilli mix at a time in about 1/4 to 1/2 cup of water.
Add to other ingredients.
Let come to boil. Reduce temperature and simmer about 10 minutes.
Keep stirring.

title: yelton's hush puppies
directions: Add well beaten egg and milk to meal.
Add hot shortening and onion just before frying.
Drop by tablespoons into hot, deep fat. Fry to a golden brown.

title: chef alley's beef stew
directions: Brown meat until golden brown.
Add flour to form a paste. Add garlic, thyme, tomatoes and water to cover.
Cook about 45 minutes, then add all other ingredients and cook until done or when meat is tender.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs; cool and shell.
Cut lengthwise.
Place yolks in bowl, mashing with fork.
Stir in all ingredients.
Using spoon, put mixture in egg whites.
Garnish with paprika. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 12.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown beef and sausage together; drain fat. Cut Velveeta in chunks and stir to melt. Add oregano to taste. Spread on party rye and place under broiler. (Edges of rye bread brown nice and crunchy.)

title: quick butter mints
directions: Mix all ingredients on low speed
