in mixer.
Do not add any liquids!
Add drop or 2 of color as desired.
Roll in long rolls 3/4-inch thick.
Let set
an
hour.
Slice	in
1/4-inch diagonal slices.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together.
Lightly beat egg yolks. Add lemon peel, juice and butter.
Mix sugar mixture and egg-lemon mixture together.
Add to milk, stirring until well blended.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks are formed.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: biscuit balls
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients to a soft dough.
Drop by teaspoon into the sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Shape into balls and place on baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix together and chill 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite veggies.

title: hawaiian hash
directions: Combine ham, sweet potatoes, mustard, ginger and juice.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Put pineapple slices on top.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening. Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Mix until the flour is moistened and dough is easy to handle.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out one part at a time on a floured board.
Dough may be covered and refrigerated for up to a week.
Dough may also be frozen. Yields pastry for 3 (9-inch) pies.

title: company corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and margarine.
Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish except cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
When almost done, top with grated cheese.

title: soft buttermilk cookies
directions: Mix
sugar
and
shortening.
Add
eggs
and
lemon flavoring. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift
flour, baking powder and salt.
Add liquid and flour alternately into
first mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough several hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: berry banana jello fruit cup
directions: Add sliced banana to slightly thickened strawberry flavor Jell-O brand gelatin or sugar-free Jell-O gelatin.
Let chill in 4 glasses.
Top with Cool Whip.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stew
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Chop all vegetables and put in large pan.
Add ground beef, juice and soup mix.
Cover and cook until done.
Stir often.

title: oven-baked beef stew
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of the flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add to meat, tossing to coat.
In skillet, brown the meat in hot shortening. Transfer to 3-quart casserole.
Drain off 1/2 cup liquid from tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Cut up tomatoes.
Add tomatoes and remaining liquid, carrots, onion, celery, chili sauce and bouillon granules.
Mix well.
Cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup flour with reserved tomato liquid.
Stir into stew along with Mexican-style vegetables and green beans. Cover and bake for 1 1/4 hours longer.

title: grandma flaugh's chocolate pie
directions: Cook milk, egg and dry ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook at slow boil 1 minute.
Add chocolate chips or cocoa, butter and vanilla and cook until dissolved and thick. Cool 20 minutes before filling a cooled pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onions in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash; add cheese and margarine while hot.
Add beaten egg and milk and mix thoroughly.
Make crumbs with Ritz crackers and stir into mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Grease pan with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix milk, eggs, oil, salt, soda, corn, chopped onion and cornmeal.
Grate cheese and chop peppers.
Add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate hermits
directions: Cream fat, add sugar and the eggs, one at a time.
Add hot water mixed with cocoa or melted chocolate, then raisins and the dry ingredients.
Drop on a greased pan and bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cornflake kisses
directions: Bring sugar and
syrup	to
a
boil; add peanut butter. Stir in cornflakes and
shape
into small balls and put on wax paper.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter or margarine to a boil in a large saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute, or until mixture forms a ball.

title: chocolate milk
directions: Put milk in blender.
Then put Hershey's in the milk.
Blend.

title: apple pie
directions: Cut up apples into little pieces and mix other ingredients with them.
Place in deep dish pie crust (unbaked)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Allow to cool slightly before adding remaining ingredients.

title: lemon slush
directions: Mix flour, nuts and butter together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add buttermilk and flour, alternating.
Add vanilla and soda; stir in pecans and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes three layers.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Pare and slice apples in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter. Mix flour, sugar (1 tablespoon), baking powder and salt together. Cut in the shortening and add milk. Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and to fit into baking dish. Cut several gashes into dough to allow steam to escape. Place over apples and press to side of baking dish or cut dough into 1 to 1 1/2-inch squares and place over apples. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serve with pudding sauce or nutmeg flavored sweetened cream.

title: baked chicken breast with horseradish cream sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour and cook, stirring, for 1 minute without browning.
Whisk in milk; bring to a boil and cook, stirring, until sauce is thick and smooth, about 3 minutes.
Stir in horseradish, sour cream, sugar, mustard, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix oil, cocoa, butter and sugar.
Blend in one egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt into oil mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll in sugar; shape into balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not overbake!
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: rhonda's broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all other ingredients and add broccoli.
Put in greased baking dish. Top with (one slice) bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat cocktail
directions: Combine the ingredients in the order given and chill.
Arrange in cocktail glasses and garnish with small sprigs of parsley.

title: million dollar salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and condensed milk together with mixer. Drain fruit and add it along with other ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir with spoon and refrigerate.

title: ham and cheese biscuit pockets
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease large cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine ham, cheese and apple.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
On prepared cookie sheet, press or roll 5 biscuits to 4-inch circles.
Place about 1/2 cup ham mixture on center of each circle.
Press or roll remaining 5 biscuits to 5-inch circles. Place each over filling.
Press edges with fork to seal.
Combine egg and water; brush over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut each in half to form pocket sandwiches; garnish with alfalfa sprouts and tomatoes to serve. Serve warm.
Makes 5 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Delicious baked over country-style spareribs.

title: chocolate mint snow-top cookies
directions: In a bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Over hot (not boiling) water, melt 1 cup Nestle Toll House mint flavored semi-sweet chocolate morsels, stirring until smooth.

title: man's cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening. Add egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add oatmeal, coconut and nuts.
Work until mixed together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Layer 1:
Mix the flour, melted oleo and chopped nuts.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: bisquick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in Bisquick, beating vigorously.
Turn dough onto surface, well dusted with Bisquick. Knead until smooth.
Form into rolls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and brush with butter.
Cover with a damp cloth.
Let rise in a warm place about 1 hour.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes until a rich brown color.
Bake at 350° or 400°.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and reserve 1 cup of juice.
Mix the pudding with the 1 cup of juice.
Add all the fruit and mix well.

title: low-fat salmon patties
directions: Drain liquid from can and save for use later.
Empty contents of can in small mixing bowl.
Remove skin or fat.
Use table fork to break into small pieces.
Add bread crumbs, beaten egg and liquid saved from can.
Make into 4 small patties.
Use Pam in skillet.
Cook on medium heat about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: carrot (raisin) pudding
directions: Cream butter and
sugar;
mix
in all ingredients until blended well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: english muffins
directions: For Bran Muffins:
Replace 2 1/2 cups of the flour with bran.

title: cheese carrots and parsnips
directions: Work 1/2 pound Cheddar cheese with 1/2 teaspoon sauce and 1/2 tablespoon onion until it is well mixed.
For each "carrot" measure 1 tablespoon of the cheese mixture and squeeze and roll between palms to a carrot-shaped cylinder.
Poke a sprig of parsley in the top.
For the "parsnips" follow the same procedure using the white Cheddar and poking a dill sprig in the top.
Chill.

title: chili rellenos quiche
directions: Stir to mix all ingredients, then pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves with tossed green salad and a side dish of Pace picante sauce (the hotter, the better, if you are entertaining me!).

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water, sugar and pineapple juice and freeze. (Best to freeze in a 5-quart bucket, like ice cream comes in at grocery store.)
Let thaw and add ginger ale.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat lightly by hand just until combined.
Stir in flour and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread batter into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Frost or glaze top, if desired.

title: holiday chicken wings(serves 4)
directions: Cut chicken wings into 2 pieces.
Remove and discard wing tips.
Bake or broil until done.
Drain on paper towels to remove most of the fat.
Combine dressing and apricot preserves in small saucepan and stir over low heat until hot and well mixed.
Combine with chicken wings, coating completely.
Spread in large glass baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: fancified egg salad
directions: Mix eggs, cheese, onion, bacon, Worcestershire sauce or soy sauce, pepper, garlic powder, mustard and mayonnaise.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and pour over meat loaf.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Don't let meat loaf get too dry.

title: grandma mag's cherry nut bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until mixture is like cornmeal.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook the sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to crumble.
Drain well. Combine sausage with the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.
Keeps like quiche.
Enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Top with slice of Swiss cheese on top of each one.
Mix the soup together (undiluted). Pour over cheese and chicken.
Cover with stuffing.
Bake 1 1/2 hours uncovered at 350°.

title: southwest beef stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown in oil in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into balls 1 1/2-inches or smaller in size.
Freeze.

title: apricot chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet(s).
Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheet(s).
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in airtight container up to 2 weeks.

title: willy's french toast
directions: Mix eggs and milk.
Mix in 2 drops of vanilla, 2 drops of almond extract and several dashes of cinnamon.
Mix by hand with fork or whip.
Heat griddle.
Grease lightly with real butter. Heat until water drops sizzle on griddle.
Dip bread long enough to coat both sides (do not soak too long), then lay on griddle. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Flip when bottom is dry.
Serve with real maple syrup.
Makes 10 to 12 slices.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 10-inch skillet.
Cook at 500° until done.

title: sweet and sour pork or chicken
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Add water if not at least 1/2 cup.
Cut pork or chicken into cubes; saute in large frying pan in oil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, lemon juice and the next 6 ingredients; stir well.
Add juice mixture and green pepper, cut into thin strips, to skillet. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes to thicken.
Run water over snow peas to thaw.
Add to skillet with pineapple chunks.
Cook 2 minutes more. Serve over cooked rice and with egg rolls.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: This recipe is made without eggs.
Cookies are very moist. Mix all ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tropical salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cracked wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
In another bowl, pour the milk over butter, molasses and cracked wheat mixture, stirring until lukewarm, then combine with yeast and water, stirring.
Gradually add half the flour and beat for 3 minutes, then add the rest of flour (needed) to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until satiny smooth.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn once.
Cover with clean cloth and place in a warm spot.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Punch down, shape into loaves and place in greased bread pans.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake for 40 more minutes.
Remove from pans to rack; cool.

title: tex-mex spaghetti pie
directions: Stir butter into hot spaghetti, add eggs and Parmesan cheese. Form spaghetti mixture into a crust in 9 x 10-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies(big batch)
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in unbeaten eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift together and stir in soda, flour and cream of tartar.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 10 dozen.
Can be baked immediately or stored in refrigerator.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in saucepan over medium heat; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add peanut butter and raw oats.
Scoop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; let cool.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add the oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and let set until cooled and firm.

title: grilled yogurt lemon chicken
directions: In a large bowl, mix together yogurt, vinegar, lemon juice, garlic, coriander, mustard, pepper, ginger, cloves and hot pepper sauce.
Add chicken, turning to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator about 1 1/2 hours. Reserve marinade.
Place chicken, skin side up, on prepared grill about 8-inches from heat. Grill, turning and basting with marinade every 10 minutes. Cook about 1 hour or until chicken is fork-tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue rub
directions: Mix all ingredients. Apply to your favorite meat before placing on the grill or in the oven.

title: sour cream beef stew
directions: Brown bacon.
Add onions, then brown the beef.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and white wine.
Bring to a boil; simmer 3/4 hour (45 minutes).
Add sour cream; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add vegetables; cook 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy baked cornbread with corn
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine egg and sour cream.
Stir in cornbread mix, salt and pepper.
Add corn; mix well.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden.
Yields 8 servings.

title: green beans (or peas) in cream sauce
directions: Add to beans and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup heavy cream.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix and pack in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Melt a 12 ounce package of chocolate chips for frosting.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour and mix well. Add milk, vanilla and coconut and pour into unbaked pie shells. Makes 2 pies.

title: baked salmon or trout
directions: Clean salmon or fish.
Remove all fat.
Combine dressing, salt and lemon juice.
Pour over fish.
Marinate at least 30 minutes and turn once (I prefer a couple hours).
Remove.
Place in greased baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch) or use cookie sheet.
Crush onions and add Parmesan cheese and sprinkle over fish.
Bake until flaky and tender, about 30 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!
Serves 6.

title: peanut bars
directions: Mix Chex and peanuts in large bowl.
Mix syrup and sugar; bring to a full boil.
Take off heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix well and pour over Chex and peanuts.
Mix well. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan; press down and cut into squares.

title: indian-style vegetable stir-fry(makes 6 servings; carb count: 6 grams)
directions: *Jalapeo peppers can sting and irritate the skin; wear rubber gloves when handling peppers and do not touch eyes. Wash hands after handling.

title: little chicken puffs
directions: In saucepan, cook green pepper, onion, garlic and curry in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mushroom soup, chicken, water chestnuts and chutney.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix together soy sauce, oil, ginger, garlic salt, syrup and pepper.
Marinate flank steaks in mixture overnight.
Grill on cooker.
Cut on diagonal.
Delicious!

title: white chocolate crisp
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt the white chocolate over water in double boiler. Pour melted chocolate over the mix. Stir quickly to coat everything.
Spread onto a waxed paper lined cookie sheet. When firm and cool, break into pieces.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook until thick.
Put into hot canning jars; seal.

title: low-fat bananas foster
directions: Slice bananas in half lengthwise; cut into 4-inch lengths. Brush with lemon juice.
Blend Butter Buds, brown sugar and banana liqueur in skillet.
Add bananas.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes, turning once.
Place in serving dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Heat rum to lukewarm in saucepan.
Pour over bananas; ignite.
Spoon over frozen yogurt.
Sprinkle Grape-Nuts over top if desired.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops lightly in hot skillet.
Remove to baking pan. Pour fat from skillet, leaving about 1 tablespoon in pan.
Add flour and dehydrated onion soup mix.
Blend in water.
Pour over chops.
Cover with foil; bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake for 30 to 40 minutes longer, or until tender.
Remove from oven.
Place chops on serving plate. Garnish with celery leaves.

title: phyllis swensons spring relish
directions: Chop vegetables.
Mix dressing ingredients and pour over vegetables.

title: bakery style icing
directions: Beat Crisco and vanilla together well.
Add milk, flour and powdered sugar.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Enough icing for 2-layer or 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: fruit salad
directions: In fruit bowl, slice bananas, add pineapple chunks and oranges. Can add coconut, marshmallows and pecans, if desired.
Top with favorite pie filling.
I prefer peach.

title: glitter salt
directions: Note:
Great recipe for birthday parties, rainy days, scouts. etc.
Makes great sand art gifts.

title: soft-fried pork
directions: Cut pork into diamonds of about 1/2 x 1/2 x 3/4-inch; mix with salt and cooking wine.
Break and beat egg in a bowl.
Add flour and stir the mixture into a smooth batter.
Add a tablespoon of peanut oil and mix well.
Put pork in.
Mix and coat well with batter.
Heat oil again and return pork to pan for another minute more of frying.
Drain.
Sprinkle on spiced salt before serving. Serves 2.

title: new hampshire fruit cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add the well beaten eggs and soda, dissolved in water.
Sift the flour and cinnamon 3 times.
Add half of the flour mixture to the butter, eggs and sugar.
Use the remaining half of the flour to mix with the chopped nuts and fruit.
Blend all of the ingredients; mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie tins.
Bake in a moderate 340° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: swedish braised short ribs
directions: Heat Dutch oven until very hot, add shortening, then meat. Cook over high heat until meat is very well browned on all sides. Add onions, with fork, push down into fat around meat; cook a minute or so, or until browned.
Add salt, pepper, 1 teaspoon sugar, allspice, bay leaves and hot water.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until fork-tender.
Remove meat to a
heated platter and keep hot.
Skim about 1/4 cup fat from liquid in Dutch oven. Stir cold water into flour, slowly add, stirring, to liquid and cook until thickened.
Bring to boil, pour over meat, serve at once.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter, add sugar, cocoa and canned milk.
Mix well, boil 3 minutes, remove from heat.
Quickly add peanut butter and vanilla until dissolved.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop onto buttered wax paper.

title: sicilian toast
directions: Slice bread into 1-inch slices.
Melt butter in olive oil. Mince garlic and basil.
Saute in butter-oil mixture.
Chop and seed tomatoes.
With pastry brush, dab bread with garlic butter mixture.
Cover bread with chopped tomatoes.
Pepper generously and sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Place under broiler until browned.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Add soup, pepper and water.
Cook about 5 minutes more.

title: boiled chicken backs
directions: Wash and clean chicken; season meat to taste.
In large Dutch oven add chicken backs, package of onion soup mix, can of tomatoes and 1/2 pot of water.
Let chicken and ingredients cook down and add 1 cup of flour to thicken, when chicken is cooked.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening.
Add sugars gradually; beat until light.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and creamed mixture; add coconut and corn flakes.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet, 1 1/2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 the amount of bacon drippings in a skillet and brown ground beef in it.
Remove to a bowl.
Add remaining bacon drippings and saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic until onion is slightly browned.
Add bay leaf, thyme, seasonings, tomato sauce and browned meat.
Simmer slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
A little water may be added if sauce is too thick.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.

title: marsetti casserole
directions: Brown beef; push to side.
Add celery, onions and green peppers.
Cook until tender.
Add sauce, tomato sauce, sugar and noodles.
Place in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken crunch
directions: In shallow pan, combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk; set aside.
On waxed paper, lightly coat chicken with flour.
Dip into soup mixture.
On another piece of waxed paper, coat chicken with stuffing.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese; add mayonnaise.
Add bacon, cooked crisp and crumbled.
Add frozen potatoes.
Stir all together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan until bubbly at 350°, 60 minutes or more.
May be reheated.
High in cholesterol, but good!

title: mom's tater tot casserole
directions: Pat ground beef into 9 x 9-inch baking pan (no salt).
Cover with mushroom soup and top with 1/2 envelope dry onion soup mix. Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger with baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion in skillet; add ground beef and continue to brown.
Add cooking ingredients to remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: grated sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: clam spaghetti
directions: Drain clam liquid into measuring cup and add chicken broth to make 1 cup.
Set aside.
Heat oil in pan and saute garlic and parsley for 1 minute.
Add clam liquid, clams, salt, pepper and simmer for 2 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in butter.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: strawberry bavarian torte(diabetic version)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add berries and allow to partially thicken.
Fold in 1 container Cool Whip.
Toss with cake cubes and place in greased (Pam) tube pan.
Chill overnight. Remove from pan and frost with remaining container of Cool Whip.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop the first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over other ingredients.
Chill.

title: chocolate kahlua pie
directions: Whip
the
butter
until creamy.
Add the melted chocolate, then
mix
in
the	sugar.	Slowly	add Kahlua, then the eggs. Pour
mixture into pie crust and refrigerate 2 hours or until set. Garnish with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients and serve cold.
Makes 3 gallons.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Pour 1 cup dried cake mix into a bowl and set aside.
Combine remaining cake mix with 1 egg and oil.
Press into bottom and 3/4 of the sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been greased.

title: sausage and egg breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Cut the crust off bread, butter both sides, cut in half and place in the bottom of greased pan. Spread cheese over bread. Brown sausage and drain on paper towel. Saute onion in a small amount of butter. Beat eggs and combine with milk, salt and pepper. Add sausage and onion to egg mixture and pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight (also suitable for freezing.) Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°. Reduce heat to 300° and cook for 10 more minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease a pie plate.
Mix all together in blender for one minute.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
May use Sweet 'N Low package for sugar.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add juice gradually.
Place alternate layers of pineapple chunks and cheese in baking dish (1 1/2 to 1 3/4-quart dish).
Cover with juice mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Good with ham or chicken.

title: very moist coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening for 10 minutes.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix well and add coconut flavoring and coconut.
Put into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Slowly add vinegar and beet juice. Stir well and heat until thickened; add beets and butter.
Heat through.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: date nut fingers
directions: In a deep saucepan, combine all ingredients except Rice Krispies and flavorings.
Cook 10 minutes.
Do not overcook. Remove from heat and add other ingredients.
Set aside to cool (when cool, it will be sticky).
Form small finger size rolls (or balls).
Dredge in confectioners sugar or finely grated coconut.

title: michie tavern's chicken
directions: Combine flour and seasonings and roll the chicken in this mixture.
Using a Dutch oven or other heavy deep pan, fry chicken in shortening at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on each side or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients (sugar through eggs) in large mixing bowl with electric mixer.
Separately mix coloring and cocoa and add to first mixture.
Separately mix last 3 ingredients and then add them to previous mixture.
Bake at 350° for 28 minutes in three greased and floured cake pans.
Top with French Frosting.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, berries and pecans. Stir just until all are moistened.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Cool in pans 5 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt and soda (mix together first).
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Cook pudding mix for pie filling using 2 cups eggnog and 1 1/4 cups milk. Cool slightly. Stir in rum and nutmeg; pour into baked pie crust. Cover surface with plastic wrap. Chill. Serve with whipped cream sprinkled with nutmeg.

title: "letcho" czechoslovakia hot dog soup
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, salt, pepper and cumin.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add turkey franks and simmer until done.
Serve in large soup bowls with French bread.

title: waldorf slaw salad
directions: Shred 6 cups green cabbage; cut apple into bite-size pieces (leave peel on).
Add raisins; mix all ingredients with slaw dressing.
Garnish with apple slices and nuts.

title: saucepan cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening in a large saucepan; stir in the brown sugar.
Allow to cool slightly. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Blend well.
Turn into a greased cookie sheet and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned corn salad
directions: Bring sugar, salt, mustard, vinegar and water to a boil.
Add cabbage, celery and green pepper.
Boil a few minutes (only until tender).
Add corn.
Chill overnight.
Drain before serving. Delicious with any meat.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: deluxe deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and put yolks in bowl.
Mash egg yolks and add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Stir in tuna or deviled ham and curry powder.
Spoon into egg whites.
Chill and serve.
Makes 6 to 12 servings.

title: turkey chowder
directions: Cook bacon by microwave (use meat rack) until crisp, reserving 1/4 c. drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside. In 3-quart casserole, cook onions in reserved drippings 3-4 minutes on High setting. Add potatoes, broth and salt. Cover, cook on high setting 10 minutes. Reduce power level to Medium High. Cook additional 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add turkey, cream, pepper and crumbled bacon. Cook covered 5-7 minutes on High setting or until heated.

title: carol's party potatoes
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream. Add hot potatoes and heat until light and fluffy. Add garlic salt and butter; mix.
If too stiff, add a little milk.
Pour into casserole and brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Dip pork in flour and fry.
You may also stir-fry about 10 minutes. Set aside.

title: dolly parton soup
directions: Cook in a large pot for 30 minutes and serve.
Only has 4 calories.

title: apple bacon cheddarwiche
directions: Grill buttered cinnamon raisin bread with cheese and apple slices.
Place bacon onto sandwich and serve closed with Caramel Dip.

title: baked chicken with gravy
directions: Preheat oven at 400°.
Place chicken, skin side up, in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix soup mix (dry), mushroom soup and water; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for approximately 50 minutes.
Spoon mushrooms over chicken and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: alligator meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, form into 1-inch balls.
Allow to set for 1 hour.
Dredge with flour and fry until brown.
Serve hot.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Put beans in a sieve.
Rinse with cold water and drain well. Add beans to onion and pickles.
Moisten with salad dressing.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine fruits and sprinkle with lemon juice; chill.
Fold in creamy mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce. Sprinkle with coconut. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften enough to mix thoroughly with garlic juice. Refrigerate until cold enough to form ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: simply sensational chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute until browned.
Reduce heat.
Pour PC Memories of Szechwan peanut sauce over chicken; cover tightly and continue cooking for 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan and keep warm.
Add cream and lemon juice to pan.
Bring mixture to a rapid boil and cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Return chicken to pan and heat through.
Serve with rice and sauce spooned over.

title: cavatine
directions: Cook macaroni 6-7 minutes. Drain and put in a greased 1 1/2 qt. dish. Add all other ingredients except cheese. Using tomato paste can, add 2 cans of water to the paste. Mix and add it and cheese to top. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: magic muffins
directions: Mix together and spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° until done.
Easy and fun for kids!

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in order given. Add enough flour to make a rather stiff batter. Add nuts, dates and cut up candy orange slices. Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour.
Makes about 3 small loaves.

title: robert e. lee salad
directions: Combine black-eyed peas, onion, green onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Add dressing and toss. Do not add salt or pepper.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a small jar.
Cover with lid and shake until blended.
Refrigerate, covered, until needed.
Shake well again before using.
Enough for a large bowl of salad greens with other veggies.

title: brisket with sauerkraut
directions: Put meat in a large pan.
Add sauerkraut, sugar, tomatoes, onion and apple.
Cover and cook 3 hours, until tender.
Check for sweet and sour taste.

title: the little mermaid dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend mayonnaise and sour cream together.
Add tuna, curry, tarragon and salt, then add Danish cheese and blend well.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.

title: bacon-cheese hot dogs
directions: Wrap American cheese slices around a hot dog and then wrap one slice of bacon around the cheese.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: chocolate treat
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil (stirring occasionally).
Boil hard for 10 minutes. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spread in well buttered 12 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: surprise cake
directions: Combine first three ingredients and pour into a buttered 9x13-inch baking dish or pan. Sprinkle marshmallows on this evenly, do not stir. Prepare cake mix by box directions and pour over marshmallows evenly. Bake according to temperature on cake mix box. Good served warm or with ice cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine these ingredients (mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter).
Place in casserole and top with a mixture of the brown sugar, flour, pecans and 1/3 cup butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt the butter; add the sugar and stir until it has dissolved.
Add the eggs.
Sift the flour and baking powder together; add that, with the vanilla, to the batter.
Coat the chocolate bits and nuts lightly with flour.
Then fold into the cake dough.
Butter a 9 x 12 1/2-inch pan and dust with flour. Bake the brownies for 30 minutes and then leave the pan in the oven for another 15 minutes.
Cut into squares while still warm. These keep well if they are wrapped in foil, once they are cooled.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, mushroom soup, peas and milk.
Put half mixture in casserole dish, then cover with a layer of potato chips; repeat. Top with chicken noodle soup.
Cover and cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, stir together flour, sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth. Stir in nuts and spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over the batter.
Bake for 40 minutes and let stand for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares and invert onto dessert plate.
Spoon sauce over each serving.
Top with ice cream.
Serves 9.
Recipe can be doubled and baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts; remove skin and bone.
Break or cut into bite size pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Add broth and butter to stuffing mix and mix until moist.
Crumble over chicken and sauce and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Mix in egg, vinegar and water.
Blend until all ingredients are moistened.
Makes four 9-inch crusts.
It will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Roll precooked, boned chicken in batter and drop in deep fat until brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Put hamburger, beans, picante sauce, corn dressing, seasoning and tomatoes in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Serve with Fritos and cheese.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown hamburger and drain.
Add sauce, water and oregano.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In small bowl, combine cottage cheese and egg.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer half noodles, half meat sauce, half cottage cheese mixture and one-third Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat; end with Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate brittle
directions: Combine butter, sugar and water in a Dutch oven.
Cook over low heat until it reaches hard-crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat and immediately pour onto 2 buttered 12-inch pizza pans, spreading to edge of pans.

title: rio grande supper
directions: Brown meat in big skillet and drain.
Add onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in corn, Cheez Whiz, barbecue sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve topped with corn chips, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.

title: bacon and water chestnuts
directions: Drain water chestnuts; cut in halves.
Cut bacon strips into thirds; roll bacon around chestnuts.
Pierce with toothpicks. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until brown.
Pour off grease.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl; pour over chestnuts.
Just before serving, bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in skillet at medium heat.
Add onions, peppers and beef.
Cook, stirring often.
Drain fat.
Drain tomatoes, measuring juice.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add liquid and spices to skillet.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Discard bay leaf.

title: kids' strawberry margarita
directions: Blend all ingredients at high speed and serve with a straw.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and Italian seasoning until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 cup pizza sauce, an additional cup of Mozzarella cheese and the peppers.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with breadsticks.
Makes 10 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown lean meat and onion first; salt and pepper to taste. Add Worcestershire sauce, tomato paste and stewed tomatoes. Simmer about 2 hours.
Last 10 minutes, add cream of mushroom soup.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Top with grated cheese (optional).

title: cherry tart
directions: Mix all ingredients together, spread on cookie sheet with fingers.
Add 3 cans cherry pie filling.
With remaining dough, roll out strips and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in strips and coat in flour, pepper and meat tenderizer.
In Dutch oven, melt Crisco and brown meat.
Remove meat.
Add soup, ketchup, water and green pepper (cut in pieces). Mix together.
Add meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: one pan dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Peel and quarter (lengthwise) potatoes and carrots.
Put on top of pork chops.
Add the can of tomato soup, can of water and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer. Simmer 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, pepper and mushrooms with spices in oil and margarine until tender.
Put shrimp in mixture and cook until very pink, about 15 minutes.
Meantime, cook spaghetti according to package directions, then add all ingredients together.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ma whit's butterscotch pie
directions: Mix in double boiler top:
sugar and flour.
Stir in milk. cook over hot water, stirring constantly until thick (about 15 minutes). Add egg yolks, slightly beaten; cook 3 minutes and add butter; cool.
Add vanilla.
Spread into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake until lightly browned.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool, then cut chicken into cubes.
Boil the 10 cups of broth and add 4 cups of rice.
Add salt to taste.
When rice is cooked, lower heat to simmer, then add lemon juice and cubed chicken. Serve with saltine crackers.

title: pea and asparagus
directions: Layer all ingredients in a casserole dish in the order listed above.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water; drain.
Place the spaghetti in a greased baking dish.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and beaten egg.
Saute ground beef, onion and green pepper in a large skillet until meat is browned; drain.
Stir into the meat the spaghetti sauce, sugar, oregano and garlic salt. Spread the cottage cheese over the spaghetti.
Top with the meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from the oven. Sprinkle Mozzarella over the top; bake for 10 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter at number 7 speed until soft.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until thoroughly blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, on number 8 speed.
Beat thoroughly before adding each egg.
Blend in flavor; add dry ingredients.
When all has been added, beat at number 3 speed thoroughly, beating batter.
Bake in slow oven at 300° to 325°.

title: caramel coconut pie
directions: Bake pie crusts and cool. Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in pecan pieces & coconut. Stir until brown (keep heat on low). Set aside for later. In a bowl, combine cream cheese and condensed milk. Beat with mixer until smooth. Take a spoon and stir in Cool Whip. Place 1/4 cream cheese mixture in each pie shell. Drizzle 1/4 jar caramel topping over each pie, then 1/4 coconut mixture over each pie. Then repeat layers of cream cheese mixture, caramel topping and coconut mixture. Cover & freeze for 8 hours. Let set for 5 minutes after removing from freezer, before serving.

title: pizza upside-down
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef.
Drain off fat and let cool 5 minutes. Add all but 1 tablespoon of the eggs to the beef, then stir in sauce.
Spread
in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with Cheddar and arrange Mozzarella on top.

title: brat
directions: This is a recipe for an upset stomach.
Eat in the order given.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Combine ingredients. Stir until smooth. Fill greased 6-cup muffin tin 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 10-12 minutes, or until brown. For Biscuits: Stir until smooth. Turn out mixture on floured wax paper. Knead several times. Flatten to 1/2 inch. Cut with biscuit cutter or glass dipped in flour. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 - 14 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Boil until thick and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
Can be cooked in microwave.

title: homemade meat loaf
directions: Brown onion, celery and garlic in margarine. Set aside to cool.
Mix meat, oats, eggs, spices and half of the tomato sauce. Add onion, celery and garlic.
Mold into loaf.
Place in a pan and pour remaining sauce over top.
Lay bay leaves on top. Sprinkle additional pepper and basil over all. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until firm to touch.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.

title: vinegar for pickled beets
directions: Mix and let come to boil, but do not boil.
Pour over cooked, tender beets.
Makes enough for three pints.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish with margarine.
Sprinkle a layer of stuffing crumbs mixed with seasonings.
Mix other ingredients with soups and top with another layer of stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: carrot-raisin slaw
directions: Put orange juice, orange peel, cider vinegar and salad dressing into a bottle.
Cover and shake well.
Pour in oil, cover and shake well.
Chill.
Shake dressing before using 1 cup salad dressing.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine the sugar, margarine and evaporated milk.
Stir the mixture on high until the mixture comes to a boil.
Turn the heat down to low and let boil about 30 minutes.
Test for soft ball stage.
(Put about 1 teaspoon of mixture into a cup of ice water. If you can form a soft ball the mixture is ready.)
Combine vanilla, peanut butter chips, peanut butter and marshmallow cream and stir vigorously until mixture is smooth.
Pour into a greased 11 x 14 inch baking dish.
When cool, cut into squares and enjoy.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, egg and then dry ingredients alternately with hot applesauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Add rice to ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee ground salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Drain pineapple (use juice and add enough water to make 1/2 to 3/4 cup).
Add to gelatin.
Let partially set.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and Cool Whip; fold in.
Line container with crushed chocolate cookies (which resemble coffee grounds).
Place the gelatin mixture carefully on the cookies.
Let stand for at least 2 hours.
Serves 9.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add other ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake in oven at 325° for 25 minutes or until coconut browns.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine. Mix all together and pour over macaroni.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground meat in olive oil.
Add onion soup mix.
Cook lasagna and drain.
First, layer noodles, meat, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one pan cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Stir all ingredients except cranberries and nuts in pan with a fork until moistened; beat vigorously 1 minute. Stir in cranberries and nuts.

title: chinese new year cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over low heat.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie plate (glass) with pastry.
Beat eggs in bowl until frothy; set aside.
Combine sugar and water in 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Place over moderate heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a full boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Gradually stir hot mixture into eggs; blend in butter and vanilla.
Turn into pie plate. Arrange pecans on pie.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 1 hour.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Blend all of the ingredients.
Chill well.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain.
Place in baking dish.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Heat these until cheese melts.
Pour over cabbage. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until hot through.

title: italian beef supper
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add salt, tomato, water and vegetables.
Bring to a full boil, separating vegetables with a fork and stirring frequently until sauce cubes are blended.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Bring again to a boil.
Stir in rice, cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan. Place topping on pumpkin mixture.

title: applesauce cookies(soft)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Add raisins.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: unfried low-fat catfish(servings:  four)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray the vegetable oil over baking sheet 3 times to coat.
Put the cornmeal, thyme and basil on a large plate and mix well.
Sprinkle just a pinch of garlic powder (1/8 teaspoon), 1/8 teaspoon of lemon pepper and 1 teaspoon of blackening seasoning on each catfish fillet.
Then coat the fillets with the cornmeal mixture of thyme and basil and transfer them to the prepared baking sheet.
Dust each fillet with 1/8 teaspoon of paprika and then cook each fillet lightly with cooking spray (Pam).
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350° for 5 minutes, until fish is golden brown and flaky.

title: vichyssoise(hot)
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent (but not brown).
Add potatoes and chicken broth; cook over moderate heat, until potatoes are mushy.
Remove from heat; mash potatoes (and juice) with potato masher, until very smooth (no lumps).
Put potato mixture into strainer and stir (and push it down) into large saucepan, until all mixture is completely through strainer.
Add milk; mix with wire whip.
Blend in salt, pepper and paprika.
Heat mixture over medium-high heat until very hot (but not boiling).
Add heavy cream and heat to very hot.
Serve immediately after garnishing with parsley.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, tossing lightly, and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: "my family's favorite"
directions: Note:
You will need crock-pot (mine happens to be a 3 1/2-quart.
If yours is larger or smaller, you may need to make some adjustments in the following:
onion soup, mushroom soup and beef broth.

title: quick dessert
directions: Put juice in one bowl, and fruit in a large bowl.
Add marshmallows to juice.
Add pudding mix to fruit and mix well. Let stand 5 minutes then combine.
Fold in Cool Whip and grape nuts.
Chill 1 hour or up to 2 days in flat pyrex or pretty serving bowl.

title: broiled shrimp
directions: Place shrimp in casserole dish, uncovered.
Melt margarine and mix with garlic.
Pour over shrimp.
Sprinkle the following over shrimp:
lemon juice, black pepper, salt, seasoned salt, thyme and olive oil.
Broil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn over and broil additional 5 minutes or until done.

title: best ever raw potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes
on
a
coarse
grater;
mix in beaten egg and
buttermilk.
Sift
dry
ingredients
together; add, all at once, to
potato mixture.
Mix very well.
Stir in melted butter.
Cook on
hot,
well-greased
griddle or frying pan; about 1/3 cup mixture per pancake or cook in waffle iron, about 3/4 cup per waffle.
Makes 8 pancakes or 4 waffles.

title: harvard beets
directions: In saucepan, put sugar, flour and salt.
Slowly stir in vinegar; add butter.
Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low.
Add beets and cook until heated through, about 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine and spread over potato mixture; bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: strawberry cake with frosting
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Roll meat cubes in flour; brown in a Dutch oven with vegetable oil.
Cover with water; add salt and bay leaves.
Simmer slowly for about 2 hours, adding water if needed, until tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Simmer for 30 minutes more or until vegetables are done and liquid has thickened into gravy.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: butter toffee
directions: Layer graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with almonds. Cook sugar and butter 2 minutes.
Spoon over almonds and crackers.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Mix pudding.
When cake is cooled, crumble one layer into punch bowl.
Top with 1/2 of pudding, pineapple, cherry pie filling, Cool Whip and then nuts.
Then repeat with the other layer of cake, remaining pudding, etc.
Garnish top with nuts. This cake will serve a lot of people.

title: diced apple cake
directions: Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-nut salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water for 10 minutes; remove from stove.
Add Jell-O, celery and nutmeats.
Pour into mold or dish. Chill until firm.

title: pickled carrots(diabetic)
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Do not overcook.
Combine everything and let set overnight.
May add cucumbers or cauliflower, etc.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown the hamburger.
Mix in the soups and enchilada sauce; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Grate the Cheddar cheese; chop the onion.
Wet the corn tortillas in hot grease; drain on paper towel and tear apart.

title: jam roll-ups
directions: Unfold the pie crust onto a lightly floured surface and spread a thin layer of jam or preserves on the dough.
With a butter knife, cut the crust into 20 pie slices.
Then roll up each wedge, starting at it's wider edge.
Chill the roll-ups for at least 1 hour so they will retain their shape during baking.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Fold in coconut, pecans and raisins.
Spoon into buttered 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.
Place marshmallows on top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: beef biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat well and drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cut biscuits in halves lengthwise.
Put meat in baking dish and cover the top with cut biscuits.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: ritzy dates
directions: Cook dates and milk until very thick.
Put on crackers.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Mix other ingredients. Spread on top of crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and minced onions in a medium bowl.
Let set at room temperature.
Spread crescent rolls in a pizza pan and bake as directed until brown.
Let cool.

title: key lime pie
directions: Crush graham crackers into crumbs.
Mix crumbs, margarine and sugar together; press into 9-inch pie dish.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pretzel mix
directions: Mix oil, Ranch dressing, garlic powder, dill weed and lemon pepper.
Pour over pretzels.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Stir and bake 10 minutes more.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13-inch pan one layer deep.
Pour package of onion soup mix over chicken.
Add the can of cream of celery soup (undiluted) over the dry soup mix.
Add the Minute rice over celery soup.
Mix 1 can water with the can of mushroom soup and add.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: orange-pineapple salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Drain crushed pineapple and oranges; mix together with jello and pour in 9 x 11-inch flat pan. Allow to set.
Beat Dream Whip, milk and vanilla pudding; spread over jello.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: seafoam delight
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water together.
Let cool.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, salad dressing, cottage cheese, nuts and pineapple.
Add to Jell-O.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill until set.

title: pepper steak
directions: Steak can be browned in oil, but I use just a little Pam. Sprinkle steak with paprika and pound to tenderize.
Cut steak in 1-inch squares and brown.
Add onion and bell pepper to steak and cook until onion begins to be transparent.
Add garlic powder, bouillon cube and 1 3/4 cups water.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes; let mixture come to a boil; mix soya sauce, 1/4 cup water and cornstarch; add to ingredients and cook until thickened.
This can be cooked early and reheated.
Serve over rice.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in bowl.
Cut in butter to make crumb mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook
and
drain
noodles.
Mix together milk and eggs. Add noodles and stir together.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle some cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchanted brownie delights
directions: This is the way to offer "deviled" eggs to the dieter.
You throw away all the egg yolks.
You will need at least 1 egg (or 2 stuffed halves) per person.
Hard-boil the eggs.
When cool enough to handle, peel, cut in half and throw away the egg yolks.
The stuffing can be your choice.
Any meat or fish salad is excellent. Try leftover, chopped vegetables bound with a little mayonnaise and mustard or low-fat crab mix.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Pat remaining mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Stir in chips.
Spread over baked layer. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together.
Make into balls; dip in sugar.
Flatten with bottom of a glass.
Bake at 325° to light brown.

title: crock pot beans
directions: Cook on high for 4 hours or low for 6 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Transfer to baking dish; top with crumbs and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine sugars and cream with butter.
Then add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and baking powder; mix.
Then add baking soda in water and mix well.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Arrange 24 frozen rolls into a greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with package of butterscotch pudding.
Melt 1 stick oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy-cheesy fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Prepare cream cheese filling.
Heat butter and cocoa in small saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted. Cool.
Beat cocoa mixture, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large mixing bowl with mixer on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, about 1 minute.
Beat in flour and salt on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, about 1/2 minute.
Beat on medium about 1 minute longer.
Stir in nuts; spread 1/2 of dough in pan and top with cream cheese filling.
Gently spread remaining dough with an over-under motion for marbling.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes.

title: banana dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In medium bowl, combine flour and butter. Spread on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.

title: bean salad
directions: Shake sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper and pour over vegetables.
This keeps for 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: chinese rice
directions: Boil water in a small saucepan.
Add rice.
Stir and remove from burner. Cover with lid.
In a medium size skillet, melt butter over medium-low heat.
Scramble eggs.
Add onion and frozen vegetables.
Stir 3 to 4 minutes. Add rice and simmer until water is absorbed.
Mix soy sauce in 1/4 cup water.
Add to rice mixture. Simmer until water is absorbed (3 to 5 minutes).

title: potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and salt. Blend well.
Press into one large or two small pans so that candy will be about 1/2 inch thick.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
(Do not allow water to boil.)
Pour chocolate on top of candy.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix sauce, cheese and soup.
Save 1 1/2 cups to pour on top. Mix in chicken; pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and olives and optionals on top.
Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: company chicken
directions: Arrange in baking dish in following order:
chicken, salt and pepper, Swiss cheese, 1/4 cup soup, 3/4 cup stuffing (prepared) and drizzle 1/4 cup melted margarine over top if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and butter in double boiler.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered foil.
Let cool.
Melt almond bark; dip caramels in and put on foil to cool.

title: three-bean baked beans
directions: Brown bacon; drain on paper towel and put in bean pot.
Pour off fat from pan, brown beef in same pan adding onions after beef begins to turn color.
Fry until beef is fully browned and onions are translucent.
Drain off all fat.
Add beef and onions to baking dish.
Stir into beef mixture the sugar, brown sugar, ketchup, barbecue sauce, mustard, molasses, chili powder, pepper and beans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican pizza
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over high heat, cook ground beef and onion until all the pan juices evaporate and the meat is well browned, stirring frequently.
Stir in the chili powder and cook for 1 minute.
Add taco sauce, salt and cumin; heat to boiling. Reduce the heat to low; cover and simmer for 5 minutes to blend the flavors, stirring occasionally.

title: cape chowder
directions: Cut fillets into 2-inch pieces; set aside.
In Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add onions; saute until golden.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add water, potatoes, carrots, Worcestershire sauce, salt, tarragon and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Lay fish on top.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender and fish flakes easily.
Scald milk.
Stir in cream.
Gradually pour into fish mixture.
Heat only until hot.
Do not boil.
Yields approximately 3 quarts.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix ingredients lightly and chill.

title: microwave scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and turn into a greased 1-quart glass casserole.
Cover with an all glass lid or plastic wrap.
Cook in microwave oven 6 to 8 minutes at High; stir occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Brown chicken, salted and peppered, in oil in heavy pot. Remove chicken to saute onion.
Place chicken back in pot, add remaining ingredients except sour cream and simmer about 1 hour. The flour blends better if it is mixed with the water before adding to chicken mixture.
While mixture is simmering, it should be covered with tight lid.
Remove lid after simmering and add sour cream.
Allow to cook slowly for 5 minutes more.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat the first three ingredients together until dissolved. Soak Knox gelatine in water for 5 minutes, then combine with mixture.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup coconut and the eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Blend;
then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let sit overnight.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make cake mix according to directions.
Mix together sugar and pineapple.
Bring to boil just until sugar is dissolved.
Poke holes in cake and pour pineapple mixture on top.
Cook pudding according to directions; pour over pineapple.
Let cool and ice with Cool Whip.

title: potato vegetable soup
directions: Combine potatoes, mixed vegetables, water and salt in large kettle.
Cover and cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain.
Cut bacon in small pieces; fry until partially cooked.
Add celery and onions and continue frying until celery and onions are transparent and bacon is crisp.
Add milk, bacon, onion and celery mixture to potatoes
Mix well.
Heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Stir in cracker crumbs before serving.

title: perfect pastry
directions: In a large bowl, mix salt with flour.
Cut in shortening to make a crumbly mixture.
Blend flour and milk together.
Turn dough into floured bowl.
Divide into 3 parts.
Place in pie pans. Prick with fork before baking.
Bake in 450 degree oven until golden brown (15 or 20 minutes.)

title: tomato vinaigrette
directions: Arrange tomato slices in an 8-inch square dish and set aside.

title: garlic-lover's shrimp
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add pepper, garlic and bay leaf.
Saut 30 seconds.
Add shrimp and salt.
Saut 3 minutes.
Remove shrimp from skillet.
Set aside. Add wine, parsley and thyme to skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook until reduced to 1/4 cup (about 1 minute).
Return shrimp to skillet.
Toss to coat.
Discard bay leaf.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cube 8 slices of bread.
Put on top of milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Raisins can be added to milk mixture and cinnamon on top of bread before baking.

title: no peek beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in small roaster or Dutch oven. Cover and bake 4 hours in a 325° oven.
Don't peek.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, pumpkin, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Grease a cookie sheet and line with wax paper (greased).
Pour batter in pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on linen cloth (not terry).
Dump cake onto towel right from oven.
Remove paper and roll cake along with the towel, jelly roll style.
Let cool 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: 1-2-3 bread
directions: Mix beer with sugar and flour.
Pour the mixture into a greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven between 30 to 40 minutes.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Place potato in saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until potato is tender.
Drain.

title: pot pie noodles
directions: Cut shortening into dry ingredients. Beat the eggs in a cup (measuring cup). Fill with milk to equal 1 cup. Add to flour mixture. Roll thin and cut into squares. Alternate with layers of meat and potatoes in any meat broth.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Combine cranberries, marshmallows and sugar.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples, grapes, walnuts and fold in whipped cream. Chill.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy sour mustard pickles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Wash tiny cucumbers. Put in jars. Pour the mixed juice over them. Cover and let set at least 2 weeks.
Will keep for months if stored in a cool place.

title: slush...frosty drink
directions: In blender, whiz up all but last 2 ingredients.
Boil last 2 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Mix with rest of ingredients and divide into 2 ice cream pails.
Freeze.
When ready to use, add 2 quarts ginger ale to each portion.
Stir well and serve while still frozen.
Serves 30.

title: guacamole salad plate
directions: Place yogurt in a strainer and drain off any liquid.
Core the tomato and chop it into small pieces.
Chop the pickled jalapeno with seeds.
Mash the ripe avocado.
Combine it with all of the above ingredients except the cucumber.
On a large plate, place chopped lettuce as a bed.
Around sides, place thinly sliced cucumbers.
In the center on an individual salad plate, place the guacamole.

title: molasses crinkle cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses, beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, mix well.
Chill thoroughly or overnight.
Shape in small balls (walnut size) and dip one side in sugar.
Place sugared side up on ungreased cookie sheet 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen large cookies.

title: chicken pie 3
directions: Cook chicken.
Pull chicken apart for pie.
Mix broth and cream of chicken soup together.
Mix chicken breasts and soup mixture together.
Put in one of the pie crust.
Take the other pie crust and lay over top of pie.
Cut around to fix pie.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers until you have 7 to 8 cups cucumbers and drain liquid from cucumbers.
Grind onions until you have 2 cups onions. Put cucumbers and onions in a container so it can drain overnight.
Next day, put vinegar and sugar in a pan; bring to a boil.
Add celery seed, turmeric and canning salt, then add ground cucumbers and onions.
Let simmer for 30 minutes, then put in jar and can.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 4 teaspoons butter in a 2 to 3-quart casserole and brown chicken pieces on all sides.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Melt 2 more tablespoons butter in casserole and pour in rice.
Remove from heat and stir the rice so that each kernel is coated with butter.
Place chicken pieces over rice.

Bring the cream, milk and stock to high heat (don't boil) in a saucepan and pour it over the chicken in the casserole. Sprinkle salt and freshly ground pepper over the chicken and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let it rest covered for 15 or 20 minutes, then serve.
Serves 4.

title: wiener-bean bake
directions: Cook limas, then mix with other beans.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover, stir and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: honey celery seed dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add honey, onion and lemon juice. Beat with electric mixer.
Add oil very slowly, beating constantly to make an emulsion.
Add vinegar.
As the mixture becomes thick, continue to beat for a few minutes after the last of the oil is added.
Chill.
Will keep very well in refrigerator for several months.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: yum yum potatoes
directions: The day before, cook unpeeled potatoes in salted water with basil leaves.
Drain and refrigerate.
The next day, peel and shred in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: mexican zucchini dish
directions: Brown vegetables; add seasonings and put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: ham-n-swiss rolls
directions: Put half of mixture on bottom of rolls.
Put on ham and Swiss cheese.
Top with bread.
Put mixture on top of rolls and heat to melt cheese.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cook noodles according to package directions. In a medium skillet over medium-high heat, brown ground beef with onion, garlic and green bell pepper. Drain excess fat. Stir in noodles, pepperoni, pizza sauce and milk; mix well. Pour this mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish. Bake for 20 minutes, top with cheese, then bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate tunnel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, substituting 1/3 cup squeeze margarine for oil. Reserve one cup of batter.
Pour remaining batter into 12 cup greased and floured Bundt pan.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer.
Blend in eggs; pour over batter in pan.
Spoon reserved batter over cream cheese mixture.
Bake one hour.
Cool.
Combine 2 tablespoons margarine, chocolate and corn syrup in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate is melted.
Pour over cooled cake.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300° to 325°.
Grease
and
flour
tube pan. Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs, sour
cream
and vanilla well. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon well and
set aside.
Pour some batter in pan. Sprinkle some
sugar/cinnamon mixture over batter. Pour more batter, sprinkle mixture.
Repeat.
Bake
1 hour. Cool; remove from pan.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat until foamy the eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder and salt.
Add to foamy mixture the zucchini and pineapple.
Add to flour mixture the nuts and raisins.
Mix well and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine; mix in sweetener, water and vanilla extract.
To this mixture add the beaten egg. Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Stir into mixture. Mix in chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop by spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake from 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Mix eggs, milk and salt.
Dip each slice of bread into mixture.
Brown both sides in butter or other fat on hot griddle. Serve hot with maple syrup, jelly or honey.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, cocoa and baking powder.
Add the melted margarine, sugar and eggs.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave baking dish that has been greased.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap.
Microwave 9 minutes on High or until brownies rise in pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled; cut into squares. Makes 12 to 15 (1-inch) brownies.

title: swiss steak
directions: In skillet, add shortening.
Skillet must be hot.
Flour steak strips.
Brown on both sides, 1 to 2 minutes.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, add other ingredients. Cover and bake 3 hours at 300°. Stir often.

title: fried catfish
directions: Fillet any catfish that are very large; wash and pat dry. Pepper lightly.
Mix cornmeal and salt; combine egg and milk.
Dip fish in egg mixture and then in cornmeal.
Heat 1/2-inch oil in a heavy skillet to 370°.
Fry fish about 5 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: pork loin with blackberries and onions
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place the sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and onions in a heavy skillet over medium heat.
Stir onions to coat them with sugar and butter.
Cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Onions should turn translucent without coloring.
Remove onions from skillet and set aside.
Melt the remaining butter in the skillet over high heat; brown pork loin on all sides.
Transfer the pork loin to a baking pan; sprinkle with pepper, garlic salt and rosemary.
Surround the loin with the onions.
Place in oven; bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; transfer to warm platter. Surround the loin with the onions; top with the blackberries on top of the hot onions.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Grease casserole dish.
Then make layers of broccoli and cheese.
Pour milk over broccoli and cheese.
Sprinkle crackers over broccoli and cheese, then drizzle melted butter over broccoli and cheese and over the crackers. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and brown lightly.

title: beef guisado
directions: Heat deep frypan and
add oil.
Add meat and brown well. Sprinkle with garlic, if desired.
Add onion, cabbage and bell pepper. Stir.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, Accent and water.
Stir well. Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or potatoes.
You may add soy sauce if desired.

title: pecan pie ii
directions: Beat eggs, syrup, sugar, oleo, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake for 45 minutes in 425° oven.

title: vanilla jumbles(cookies)
directions: Beat light.
Roll with hands or drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until edges start to turn brown.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease a medium size baking dish.
Beat eggs in a large bowl. Add
sugar,
cinnamon,
salt
and
vanilla.
Add melted butter and milk.
Halve each biscuit and place in baking dish, brown
sides up.
Pour
mixture
over biscuits, then sprinkle with a little more sugar and
cinnamon.
Bake
in
a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp to die for(literally)
directions: Steam shrimp until almost cooked (will turn light orange).
In a pan saute, with extra virgin olive oil, all chopped garlic to taste (don't worry if it browns).
Add 4 tablespoons of shrimp broth, salt and spices.
Reduce.
Add shrimp to pan.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons of butter, 2 tablespoons of broth and 1/2 glass of beer.
Reduce.
Add, right before serving, more broth and beer to taste.
Let bubble.
Throw in 2 more tablespoons of butter.
Serve over 3 or 4 medallions of hot French bread.
Laugh all the way to the next cardiovascular surgeon.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and dash of pepper.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with paprika. Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer, or until done.
