title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender; drain.
Layer carrots, green pepper and onion in dish.
Blend sugar, soup, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire and salt to taste.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover dish tightly.
Refrigerate at least overnight or up to 1 week.
Remove carrots with slotted spoon to serve.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix together. Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° until done, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spectacular egg casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking casserole dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a large casserole dish or roaster with cover.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: mock cheese souffle
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard.
Layer bread and cheese in a casserole, ending with bread.
Pour egg mixture over. Let stand in refrigerator for at least 10 hours, or overnight. Bake approximately 1 hour at 275°.
Bake in a pan of water (have casserole room temperature before baking).

title: pot roast
directions: Mix flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper; rub on the meat.
Melt shortening in a large skillet and brown meat over medium heat slowly.
Drain off fat and add water and vinegar.
Cover and simmer until tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours, adding a little water, if necessary.

title: olive-nut sandwich spread
directions: Put all ingredients in a small bowl and blend well.
This will stay fresh in refrigerator for weeks.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Soften almond bark on top of double boiler. When softened, stir in all other ingredients. Spoon 1 heaping teaspoonful at a time onto wax paper. Leave on paper for 2 hours and refrigerate.

title: easy red and green pepper steak
directions: In a medium-size bowl, combine the soy sauce, sherry, vinegar and ginger.
Add the steak and toss well to coat.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Margarine and Sugar together.
Add Eggs one at a time, beat well.
Sift Flour, Salt and Baking Soda together.
Add alternately to creamed mixture with Sour Cream.
Add Vanilla and beat well.
Fold in the Coconut.
Pour in a well greased and floured Bundt or Tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven 300 degrees for 1-1/2 hours or until done.

title: red velvet squares
directions: Mix and spread into greased jellyroll pan.

title: lemon gems
directions: Combine flour, sugar and lemon peel in bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Spread in greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
Pat down.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until light brown.

title: newspaper clipping preservative
directions: Pour the club soda into a large bowl.
Drop the Milk of Magnesia tablet into the club soda and let it sit overnight to dissolve.
Place the cookie sheet on a flat surface, then pour in 1/4 inch of preservative solution.
Place newspaper clippings in liquid and let set until thoroughly saturated.
Remove clippings and lay them out to dry on a flat surface.
Makes 1 quart.
This preservative will prevent any clippings from turning yellow as long as the clipping is kept out of direct sunlight.

title: pizza skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper. Drain.
Stir in pizza sauce and soup.
Blend well.
Stir in water and pepperoni.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in uncooked noodles. Cover.
Cook over medium heat until pasta is tender, stirring frequently.
Uncover.
Cook additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: basil cherry tomatoes
directions: In a bowl, combine the tomatoes, basil, oil, salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Serve on lettuce if desired.

title: abercrombie's little league stew
directions: Cook in covered skillet in oven at 300° for 4 hours.

title: italian-style pork chops(costolette di maiate italiano)
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Mix salt, pepper and garlic in a bowl.
Rub on pork chops.
Heat oil in a large skillet and brown chops on both sides.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, mushrooms, oregano and tomato juice to skillet.
Stir.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 30 minutes.
(If you add sausage, brown it in a separate pan and drain.
Add to skillet during the last 10 minutes of cooking.)
Serves 4.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and frozen lemonade together until well blended.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Take out of freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine and spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until crusty. Cream cream cheese and sugar and blend in 6 ounces whipped topping.
Pour onto cooled crust.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix batter up real good, then drop corn dog in hot oil.
Brown real good.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook without stirring to 260° or until mixture hardens in ice cold water.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour
oil
in
large
skillet;
add
chopped
onion and pepper.
Cook
until
tender and slightly brown; add all other ingredients, continue cooking until bubbly.
Remove from heat; pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. I use a large black skillet to
brown peppers and onions, then add other ingredients and bake in same skillet.

title: patty's no peek chicken
directions: Mix together rice, cream of chicken, cream of mushroom soup and water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle seasoned salt over cut up chicken to taste and lay on top of mixture. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: seven layer cookie bars
directions: Melt one stick of oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Make layers of ingredients in the following order:
graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in 2-inch squares.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Fry and cool bacon.
Chop into pieces and set aside.
Beat egg, sugar, mustard and vinegar together.
Stir into bacon and bacon grease; cook until thick.
Pour over lettuce while hot and stir until lettuce is wilted.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix frozen vegetables, Cheez Whiz, uncooked rice, soup, onions, etc.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monte christos
directions: Prepare mixture of milk, eggs, pepper and salt (for dipping bread).
Heat griddle.
Dip and cook all bread (French bread style and on one side only).
Turn bread over, placing ham and cheese slices on cooked side.
Add second slice (placing cooked side down against ham and cheese).
Finish cooking, turning sandwich over to cook on both sides.
When done, garnish with powdered sugar. Serve sandwiches hot.

title: sour cream cupcakes
directions: Add soda to flour.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat. Add flour and soda; beat.
Add sour cream.
Preheat oven to 350°. Fill muffin cups little over 1/2 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Check before removing from oven.

title: maryland style crab cakes
directions: Begin by buying the freshest 1 pound lump crab meat available, then handle the mixing so very gently in order not to break up the lumps.
Beat egg, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, seasoning, parsley flakes, dry mustard, mayonnaise and salad dressing.
Break bread into small pieces and, along with the crab meat, gently fold into the egg-spice mixture.
Shape into slightly flattened patties and chill.
Fry or broil until golden brown on each side and serve. Yields approximately 6 (3 1/4 ounce) crab cakes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in buttered baking dish. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes.

title: indian pudding
directions: Combine 3 cups milk and maple syrup in saucepan and place over medium heat.
Heat until just boiling.
Add butter.
Combine cornmeal, ginger and nutmeg in separate bowl.
Gradually stir cornmeal mixture into hot milk.
Reduce heat to low and cook until thickened, about 10 minutes.
Fold in currants.
Spoon mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Pour remaining 1 cup milk over pudding.
Do not stir.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or until all the milk has been absorbed and top is golden brown.
Top with ice cream.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and drain; add Italian seasoning. Add tomato sauce plus 3/4 can of water, tomato paste and sugar. Simmer on low. Boil noodles until done; drain and separate. Layer mixture of sauce, noodles, and cheese. Sprinkle more Italian seasoning and Parmesan cheese on top for extra flavor. Bake at 375° 30 to 40 minutes.

title: clay pot mezetti
directions: Soak clay cooking pot and lid in warm water for 15 minutes. Place ground beef, green pepper, onion, celery and garlic in pot. Cover with water-soaked lid.
Cook on High in microwave for 6 minutes.
Drain off excess liquid.
Sprinkle noodles on meat mixture.
Stir together in a bowl the chili powder, paprika, salt, tomato soup, mushroom soup, mushrooms and water.
Pour mixture over meat and noodles.
Re-cover and microwave on High for 10 minutes, then on 50% power for 15 to 18 minutes or until noodles are cooked.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini(serves 4 to 6 people)
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk and seasonings.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, minced onion, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise; chill.
Mix cocktail sauce and chili sauce and put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Rinse and drain minced clams; put on top of sauce mixture.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours and serve with crackers.

title: reggie's wedges
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on muffin halves.
Freeze on cookie sheet and then put in plastic bag to store.
To serve, heat about 10 minutes at 350° and cut into fourths.
Very tasty.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Set power on High.
In micro-safe dish, heat onions, covered, for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 minutes.
Stir in salt, basil and pepper.
In small bowl, melt butter; stir in bread crumbs and paprika.

In 2-quart casserole dish, alternately layer half the tomatoes, onions and cheese; top with remaining tomatoes, onions and cheese. Place bread crumb mixture on top and cook, covered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes.
Standing time 5 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Soften yeast in water, add flour and stir to mix. Put in a glass, ceramic or china container with a loose lid.
Be sure the dish is as big as the starter expands.
Let set at room temperature stirring once or twice a day for 3 days.
The starter will work and have a definite sour odor.
After the starter has soured, it can be stored in the refrigerator until used.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Mix well together. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Dust with 10x sugar.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine meats, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, egg and milk.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: Put cranberries and apple through food chopper.
Use coarse blade.
Quarter orange and lemon, do not remove skin.
Do remove seeds. Put through food chopper.
Use fine blade.
Add with sugar to apple/cranberry mixture and blend well. Chill several hours before serving with meat, fish or poultry.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: In large
glass bowl, layer fruit, one at a time.
Whip together cream
cheese,
prepared
Dream
Whip
and packets of Equal.
Spread whipped mixture over fruit and top with pecans.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Pour 1 can beans in buttered baking dish. Combine sugar and mustard; sprinkle half on beans. Add other can of beans; add remaining sugar and mustard. Place bacon and catsup on beans. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix sugar, potato flour and warm water; let Starter stand out of refrigerator 8 to 12 hours, until very bubbly.

title: tami's basic pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla, almond and lemon.
Then add flour.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: classic georgia pecan pie
directions: Lightly whisk eggs in a medium bowl. Add sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and melted butter. Stir with a wooden spoon to combine well. Stir in pecans. Pour filling into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a preheated 350° oven 45 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean. Let cool on wire rack. Yield: 1 pie, 6 to 8 servings.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, ground oatmeal (measure out 5 cups, then grind), salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add flour-oatmeal mixture to butter mixture.
Add chips and ground Hershey bar.
Three cups nuts may be added, if desired.
Shape into the size of golf ball and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda; set aside.
In medium bowl cream shortening and peanut butter until well blended.
Add sugars; beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg. Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sour pie cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and add to other juices.
Add sugar and bring to a rapid boil.
Pour this hot mixture over jello and gelatine; congeal.
You may wish to add nuts, coconut, marshmallows, etc.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer pans sprayed with nonstick spray.
When cake is done, break half into punch bowl.
Make pudding mix with milk; pour half of it over broken cake.
Add pie filling, pineapple and half the bananas.
Mix whipped topping and nuts; put half of this over the bananas.
Repeat layers, ending with topping-nut mixture. Decorate with cherries on top.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours. This amount amply serves 25 people.
For smaller amount, halve the recipe.

title: frozen lemon dessert
directions: Combine and spread over bottom of 8 x 11-inch pan.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with bread crumbs and milk.
Make into balls and brown.
After meatballs are brown, place in casserole and pour sauce over it.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cut cake into small slices and place in dessert dish.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar in a separate bowl.
In another bowl, mix Dream Whip according to instructions.
Mix sugar and cream cheese with Dream Whip.
Pour mixture on top of cake.
Cover with cherries.

title: cheese ball
directions: With a fork, cream the cream cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients, reserving 1 cup of pecans.
Mix well by hand.
Let the mixture harden in the refrigerator for 45 minutes.
Remove and shape into one large or two small balls.
Roll in the reserved pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and flour, then flavoring.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: holiday potato dish
directions: Remove skins and cut potatoes into small, bite-size pieces. Saute onion in margarine.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix well.
Turn into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with corn flakes and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: For crust, cook spaghetti according to the package directions, except omit the cooking oil and salt.
Drain well. Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl stir together the 2 egg whites, the parmesan cheese, and margarine.
Stir into the hot cooked spaghetti.
Spray a 9 inch pie plate with nonstick coating. Arrange spaghetti mixture evenly in the bottom and up the sides of the pie plate.
In another bowl, stir together the remaining 2 egg whites and the drained cottage cheese.
Spread cottage cheese mixture over the crust.
Set aside.
In a large skillet cook the meat, onion, and green pepper till meat is brown.
Drain off fat. Stir in the tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, and salt.
Heat through.
Spoon over cottage cheese mixture in crust.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with the mozzarella cheese.
Bake about 5 minutes more or till the cheese melts and the crust is set.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 5 servings.

title: hungarian potato-pepper stew
directions: The front of today's Paul's Place in Weldon was the front of the shower house in old Kernville.
It was moved when the water began rising from the dam.

title: turkey or chicken hot dish
directions: Prepare rice (instructions on box).
Put rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next add chicken or turkey, then broccoli.
Add Cheddar cheese and last 2 cans of cream of chicken soup.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix salt and flour with pastry cutter or two knives.
Cut in margarine until fine crumbs form.
Sprinkle water over flour mixture while tossing with fork to blend well.
Press dough firmly into ball.
On lightly floured surface, roll out 12-inch circle. Fit into 9-inch pie pan.

title: outer banks crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into cakes and fry in margarine until brown, turning once.
Serve hot.

title: korean egg rolls
directions: In a pan, fry pork, beef or chicken; drain fat.
Finish frying with garlic, ginger, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In a large bowl combine cabbage and chives.
Add meat mixture, a little more salt, pepper and soy sauce, if desired.
Place this mixture in egg roll and roll up, using water to close egg roll tight.
Deep fry 1 minute and serve hot.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir until completely dissolved.

Fold in pineapple, bananas, nuts and strawberries. Pour half of mixture into square 9 x 9-inch pan and let congeal. When solid, spread sour cream over it and pour the remaining half of jello mixture over sour cream and chill until solid.

title: broccoli-ham chowder soup
directions: Wash broccoli.
Place broccoli and 1/2 stock in large kettle. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 7 minutes or until tender.
Remove broccoli.
Add the remaining stock, milk, salt, cheese and pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir.
Stir in cream, cheese, butter and broccoli.
Heat until the cheese melts, but do not boil.
To make thick, add 4 to 5 tablespoons cornstarch.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: cookie salad
directions: Stir all together and garnish with some crushed cookies. Chill until set.

title: denise's chicken soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on low temperature until onion and celery are tender.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Place
tomatoes in unbaked shell.
Mix remaining ingredients together
and
pour
over tomatoes.
Place unbaked pie crust on top of pie and bake at 425° for about 60 minutes.

title: melinda's parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine in Ziploc bag the last 4 ingredients.
Melt the margarine in a large baking dish.
Rinse and drain the potatoes. Shake the potatoes in "flour mixture."
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes on each side.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Put in 9-inch deep pie crust (baked).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Put cream and sugar in 4-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 13 minutes.
Quickly add pecans, margarine and vanilla; stir.
Spoon onto a sheet of foil.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar gradually while still beating.

Gradually add oil. Mix together all dry ingredients and add alternately with zucchini to egg mixture. Add nuts and vanilla after final addition. Bake in greased and floured bread pans at 350° for 1 hour. Cool in pan 10 minutes and then remove from pan and continue cooling on rack.

title: layered salad
directions: On a large platter or in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch or larger dish, arrange the following ingredients in order: spinach, water chestnuts, celery and onions.
Spread mayonnaise over top. Sprinkle with sugar.
Place in refrigerator overnight!
Arrange avocado and tomato slices in alternate rows.
Top with crumbled bacon, then Parmesan cheese.
Cut through all layers to serve. Serves 8.

title: baked, candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes about 1 hour at 400° in oven.
Peel the potatoes.
To candy them, slice potatoes and put a layer of them on the bottom of the dish.
Sprinkle white or brown sugar (or both) over potatoes.
Put pats of butter on top.
Repeat the layers.
Use 1 to 1 1/2 cups of sugar and about 1 stick margarine or butter for a long, narrow baking dish.
Sprinkle a little ginger on the very top.
Sprinkle water over mixture, making sure all sugar is dampened.
Have the water come up to about 1/2 the thickness of the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Makes sure they cook through.

title: ruby's sausage fondue
directions: Put cubed bread in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Brown and drain sausage and put on top of cheese. Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk, mustard and Tabasco.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, dilute soup in 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over cold mixture and bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours, until set.
Serves 8 to 12.
Wonderful for brunch!

title: nutty cheese bar
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir together the cake mix, butter and 3/4 cup pecans.
Press into pan.

title: teen bean bake(most kids like this one.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut wieners in 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix in baking dish with beans.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Combine in a large bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in corn meal, egg and remaining ingredients, all at once.
Stir just enough to combine.
Spoon over beans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Line a 13 x 9 baking pan with waxed paper and spray with Pam. Set aside.

title: tony's tiger bites(child-approved)
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Add Frosted Flakes cereal, stirring until well coated.
Using a buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into 1 1/2 x 2-inch bars.
Yield:
32 bars, 90 calories per serving.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts and chocolate chips, together. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili sauce
directions: Wash vegetables before preparing.
Remove seeds and white portions from peppers before chopping.
Combine vegetables, sugar, salt and cayenne pepper in a heavy pot.
Place over low heat; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, about 2 hours or until mixture thickens.
Add spices (tied in cheesecloth) and vinegar.
Cook until very thick.
Pour immediately into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal at once.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: triple chocolate delight
directions: Microwave:
Microwave all but 3 squares of the chocolate with 1/4 cup milk in large microwave-safe bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring once.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs in buttered casserole dish.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes at 375° or until brown.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from oven and cool.
Form 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: billy goats
directions: Stew raisins in water to plump.
Add soda, let stand.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add raisin mixture.
Fold in dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° on greased baking sheet.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: leave it to beaver brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan over low heat, heat butter and chocolate squares until melted.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until blended.
Stir in flour, vanilla and nuts.

title: moussaka(hamburger-potato)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook ground beef and onion in skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, oregano, cinnamon, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix sauce mix, milk, water and margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; cool 2 to 3 minutes.
Gradually stir sauce into mixed eggs. Grease baking dish 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Layer half each of the potatoes beef mixture and cheese in dish; repeat.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving (6 to 8 servings).

title: chocolate peanut clusters with pudding
directions: Mix in 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Cook and stir to a full boil. Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils 3 minutes. Take off heat. Stir in 1 cup salted peanuts. Beat until candy starts to thicken. Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper. Makes about 24 clusters.

title: scotch broth
directions: Trim fat from lamb; cut into 3/4-inch pieces.
Heat lamb, water, barley, salt and pepper to boiling in Dutch oven.
Remove heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add vegetables.
Cover and simmer until lamb and vegetables are tender (approximately 30 minutes).
Skim fat from broth if necessary.

title: crispy corn cakes
directions: In medium bowl, pour boiling water over cornmeal.
Let cool. In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Mix egg, milk and margarine with cornmeal mixture. Stir into flour mixture until blended.
Mixture will be thin.

title: french toast
directions: Put butter in frying pan and let melt.
While butter is melting, beat eggs for about 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Dip bread into eggs and cover both sides.
Put into pan and let cook until brown.

title: macaroni salmon croquette
directions: Beat eggs; roll croquette in cracker crumbs, then egg, then cracker crumbs again.
Cook macaroni in hot water until tender. Drain; rinse with cold water.
Combine butter, flour, salt and milk.
Cook until thick; add salmon and macaroni.
Chill and form cakes.
Fry until brown.

title: banana pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, salt, egg yolks, butter and flavoring. Cook slowly, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add half of mixture into cooked pie crust.
Slice bananas, lengthwise, squeeze lemon juice over top and add rest of pie filling.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Saute
meat
and onion together until meat turns white. Pour off
fat
drippings.
Grease skillet as for regular corn bread; heat and sprinkle with dry corn meal.
Mix the first 8 ingredients and pour half of the batter into skillet.
Arrange meat
and onion, that have been sauteed, on top of the batter in
the skillet.
Arrange
grated
cheese
on top of meat and onion.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: different pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Beat in sugar and baking powder.
Stir in cracker crumbs and chopped pecans.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barley casserole
directions: Saute barley and onion in butter until barley is light brown. Add other ingredients.
Stir well and pour into greased dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, adding water if needed.
Or microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Cover bottom of pan with rolls.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes; cool.
Mix the cream cheese, Miracle Whip and dressing mix together; spread over rolls.
Sprinkle veggies and cheese over cream cheese mixture; press down on veggies.
Chill 1 to 2 hours. Cut into small bars.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Pour cider and juice in percolator and place all remaining ingredients in basket of percolator.
Follow percolator directions for coffee.

title: yorkshire pudding for beef
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
After removing a rump roast from its cooking pan, return pan to oven while gently mixing ingredients in a small bowl.
Remove pan with drippings carefully.
Add batter to pan and replace in oven.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
It's done when it puffs up like a popover.
Cut into squares to serve and top with beef gravy.
(A 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan works well.)

title: slaw
directions: Mix together.
Let stand before serving.
Keeps for several days.
Great with barbecue or beans.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs till smooth.
Very carefully add sour cream and vanilla.
Slowly add sifted flour, salt and baking powder.

title: mushroom and barley chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables and barley are tender.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, salt, shortening, mashed potatoes and spices.

title: cold soup
directions: Put cucumber, watercress and onion in Cuisinart (food processor).
Chop finely with steel blade.
Add salt, pepper and buttermilk.
Chill thoroughly.
Easy and delicious.
Garnish with chives or parsley.
Serve with French bread, toast or crackers.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil water; add tea bags and remove after steeping.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Leave cloves and cinnamon sticks in mixture.
Serve warm.
Never boil.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Chill milk and whip.
Prepare Jell-O with water and juice. Mix it all together; pour into dish and chill.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Melt jelly.
Add chili sauce.
Stir in sausage; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve warm as an appetizer.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs in mixer or by hand.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in crushed bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake in moderate oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in frying pan with butter over medium heat.
Cook for 20 minutes, turning halfway through.
Remove to a plate.
Add chicken broth to pan juices to make 1 cup chicken broth.
Stir together light cream and flour; add to broth.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more.
Stir in Dijon mustard.
Spoon some sauce over chicken; pass remainder.

title: quick corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove to a paper towel to drain. Saute onion in drippings until tender. Add broth, water, potatoes; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add salt and pepper; mix well. Add corn and 3/4 cup milk. Combine flour and remaining milk until smooth; add to soup. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Garnish with bacon, cheese, and parsley if desired.

title: reece peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter; mix rest of ingredients with butter.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Pour mixture onto cookie sheet; press firmly down. Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.
Garnish with sliced tomatoes or cherry tomatoes.

title: grape salad
directions: Clean and dry grapes. Combine sour cream, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese for a creamy mixture. Pour over grapes in a bowl. Chill in refrigerator. Sprinkle with chopped pecans before serving.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Put all three ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook until meat is done, 3 to 5 hours.
Makes its own gravy.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Reserve chicken broth.
Place in saucepan chopped chicken breasts, can of cream of chicken soup and chopped peppers.
Heat thoroughly.
Heat corn tortillas in chicken broth just until semi-soft.
Place spoonful of chicken mixture on corn tortilla, then top with onion and cheese.
Roll and place in casserole dish. Top with enchilada sauce and additional cheese.
Heat at 350° until cheese has melted and enchiladas are hot and bubbly.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir until a ball forms.
Knead when cool.
Place in airtight container.

title: four soup casserole
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add hamburger and fry until done.
Cook noodles in salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add soups and hamburger to the cooked noodles.
Put into 2 casserole dishes and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Combine vegetables and stir in vinegar mixture.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 4 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: fusilli alla franco falcone(spiral macaroni with tuna)
directions: Drain the oil from the tuna into a casserole or a deep-sided pan that will go on top of the stove.
Add the garlic; place over medium heat and fry gently.
When it starts to sizzle, add tuna and break it up with a fork.
Let cook just for a minute to warm the tuna through.

title: rice surprise
directions: Cook rice.
Prepare sauce; coat bottom of pan with sauce. Place a layer of rice in pan.
Put more sauce on top.
Thin slice hard-boiled eggs,
shred ham and dice Mozzarella; place these ingredients on top of rice, leaving a little Mozzarella on side for later use.
Place another layer of rice, Mozzarella and sauce; sprinkle grated cheese.
Add a little water for a little moisture on top.
Bake at 300°
just enough for Mozzarella to melt and for rice mixture to warm up.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots 15 minutes. Add pepper and cook 3 more minutes. Drain off water. Drain pineapple and keep juice.
Add water to make 1/3 cup liquid.
Combine pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce, salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Add carrots and peppers.
Mix together and warm.

title: crock-pot turkey
directions: Put turkey in crock-pot, thick side down, and pour other ingredients on top.
Cook 12 hours, alternating between high and low temps.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and mix.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Shape into balls.
Bake at 325° on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan after cooling.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: easy salmon pie
directions: Drain liquid from salmon and save.
Remove bones from salmon. Prepare instant potatoes for 8 servings using reserved salmon liquid as part of the water.
Combine salmon and potato.
Place 1 pie crust in pie pan.
Pour salmon mixture in and cover with second crust.
Bake 25 minutes in 425° oven.

title: date salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Cream.
Add dates, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Mix and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: shoe peg corn dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Serve with large corn chips.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese until well blended. Add Cool Whip. Layer 2 sliced bananas in each pie shell and 1/2 of the blueberry pie filling, saving enough mixture for the second shell. Chill and serve.

title: carrot potato scallop
directions: In 2 quart saucepan, melt butter; saute onion. Stir in flour, salt and dill. Gradually stir in milk. Cook until thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in parsley. Put carrots and potatoes in baking dish. Pour sauce over and bake at 350° until done.

title: russian dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Refrigerate.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Set oven at 350° then grease and flour a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Continue to beat until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat well, stirring in applesauce.
Add sifted dry ingredients, stirring only enough to blend.
Pour into pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes or until cake springs back when touched. Cool in pan 5 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on a rack. Frost with Butter Frosting.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Boil together sugar, cornstarch and water until thickened. Add peach jello (dry) and let cool. Add fresh peaches and pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with peach slices.
Refrigerate.

title: cheesy rice and broccoli
directions: Bring broccoli and water to a boil in medium saucepan; separate broccoli with fork.
Stir in Velveeta cheese.
Reduce to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover, remove from heat and let stand for approximately 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Combine egg white, grapefruit juice concentrate and hot sauce in a small bowl, stirring well.
Set aside.
Crush crackers to make 1/3 cup crumbs.
Combine crumbs, cheese and sesame seed in a small bowl, stirring well.
Dip fillets in egg white mixture; dredge in crumb mixture.
Arrange fillets in an 8-inch square baking dish that has been coated with cooking spray.
Drizzle margarine evenly over fillets.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: jerry's raspberry cheese dip
directions: Combine everything in a blender or food processor with steel blade until very smooth.
Transfer to a bowl.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until cold.
Serve with fresh fruit (pears, oranges, apples, etc.).

title: baked potato soup
directions: Heat oven to 350° and bake the potatoes until fork-tender. Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Slowly blend in flour with a wire whisk until thoroughly blended.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, coconut and pecans; beat 1 minute.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Spread marshmallow cream over cake while cake is still hot.
Let cake cool before icing.

title: roast
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper and sauce over roast.
Mix soups and mushrooms together.
In large baking pan, bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, depending on tenderness.

title: easy old fashioned split pea soup
directions: Wash peas and place in a large saucepan.
Add water, chicken broth, ham shanks, carrots, onion, celery and butter to peas. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours. Stir in milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with croutons and parsley.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cut a pie pumpkin in half; clean out seeds.
Place in a crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours on high or place flat side down on a cookie sheet or round side down and cover top with foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until soft or put one half at a time in a plastic bag in the microwave; cook at least 6 minutes or until soft.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Spoon 1/4 cup batter into each cone.
Sit cones on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix these ingredients together	well
and stir into the first mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and pour into baked pie crust.

title: carrot salad
directions: Slice carrots.
Cook until tender.
Drain and pour liquid over carrots.
Let set overnight.
Can keep 5 weeks.

title: chicken sour cream casserole
directions: Boil chicken (reserve 1/4 cup broth).
Remove from bone and tear into bite size pieces.

title: old-fashioned butter roll
directions: Make favorite biscuit dough and roll out on board.
Cut margarine into pats and place over dough.
Sprinkle on sugar and desired spice.
Fold dough over, or roll in jelly roll fashion. Seal edges.
Put into pan and add enough milk to cover (may need more than required amount).
Cook until done, approximately 30 minutes.
Add more milk during cooking if needed.
Should be saucy and thick like cobbler.
